commit_message:
Destructive test for neutron l3 agent

Pacemaker should restart neutron l3 agent
Scenario:
1. Deploy Ha with neutron
2. Pick up host where l3 agent is running
3. Turn off host
4. Wait some time
6. Create several vms to be sure that vms receive ip addresses
(Performed by OSTF connectivity tests)

Partially fix bug: https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1269806
Implements first scenario

Related-bug: #1269806
Change-Id: I30d06753b72842e0db03f96914029f5d2dec8502

commit_message:
Resolution blessing designated sections guidelines

In order to make progress, the DefCore subcommittee of the OpenStack
Foundation Board of Directors requires that the Technical Committee
defines and approves a set of base selection principles for "designated
sections".

This proposal is based on the summary of the 2014-03-28 meeting:
https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/openstack-designated-sections

commit_message:
Add a flag to allow for serial console on the seed VM

Setting USE_SERIAL_CONSOLE to 0 (the default) preserves previous
behaviour - no serial console will be configured.

Setting it to any other value will cause the serial console to be
configured.

Change-Id: Ic714402e5913795be5890e997d82c9ce37c1abac

commit_message:
Updates hadoop-hdp to use new project name in URL

This patch modifies the download URL used in the
  hadoop-hdp/source-repository-hadoopswift file to use a URL that
  includes the new project name.
This change is required by the project renaming effort, and the
  Hortonworks URL for this rpm is already available.  This change
  references the updated URL.

Closes-Bug: #1302755

Change-Id: I25021f89ca4ee38d7a8fb02fdffe57cdb2eb90a1
(cherry picked from commit d87fa27722465526810ba587899ed13638d5796e)

commit_message:
Allow address_for default family to be overridden

When IPv6 is wanted as the default interface address family, allow
single override to make that change.

Implements: blueprint ipv6-support

commit_message:
Updates hadoop-hdp to use new project name in URL

This patch modifies the download URL used in the
  hadoop-hdp/source-repository-hadoopswift file to use a URL that
  includes the new project name.
This change is required by the project renaming effort, and the
  Hortonworks URL for this rpm is already available.  This change
  references the updated URL.

Closes-Bug: #1302755

Change-Id: I25021f89ca4ee38d7a8fb02fdffe57cdb2eb90a1

commit_message:
Make DB scheme be compatible with MySQL, PostgreSQL and SQLite

PostgreSQL didn't worked with BLOB data type so more universal
LargeBinary was used

MySQL failed to create index on VARCHAR(512) column on InnoDB engine
because of internal limits. Column was used for fully qualified class names
that cannot have international characters so ASCII collation was used
for that column making 1 char = 1 byte and thus fitting to MySQL length limit

Change-Id: I3e2e70476a5092e22874fa69f4fa81e9d19fb419

commit_message:
ml2/enable_security_group should not affect the firewall driver

When using ml2/enable_security_group at the moment the parameter
firewall_driver in the section securitygroup is set to the value
of ml2/enable_security_group. That's strange.

I think when using ml2/enable_security_group the parameter
enable_security_group in the section security_group should be set
to the value of ml2/enable_security_group.

The value of the firewall_driver in the section securitygroup
should be set by ml2/firewall_driver.

Change-Id: I06f7e5ca392dfbc5fadfafe5971f8c0e96ee65ba

For that matter, there is also a way to download the current patch set from Gerrit as a git branch, so you could have blown away your entire repository, recreate it, then pulled in the patch set from Gerrit into your topic branch to continue working on it.

commit_message:
Support IPv6 when booting instances

When nova uses neutron, IPv6 addresses may be allocated.  This ensures
those addresses are supported.the patch to modify nova is
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/74252/

Change-Id: I2468d3bcaca9122e5d3f9c98044d57f623630dc3
Closes-bug: #1267685

commit_message:
Prevent alarm_id in query field of getting history

The ceilometer CLI support alarm_id in query field of getting alarm
history.
But it will raise error when invoking the db function get_alarm_changes.
Getting history of an alarm, the alarm id is required, so we needn't allow
the alarm_id in query field of getting alarm history.

Change-Id: I968b5bbcbc5af18a737b63598b63c1caa78d187e
Closes-bug: #1290809

run_tests.sh --unittest-only current issues a warning that
`muranoapi/tests/functional` can't be found, and tries to run the
tests in functionaltests, which require tempest and a running server.

commit_message:
Correct --unittest-only test behavior

run_tests.sh --unittest-only current issues a warning that
`muranoapi/tests/functional` can't be found, and tries to run the
tests in functionaltests, which require tempest and a running server.

Changes run_tests.sh to exclude `functionaltests` instead.

Change-Id: I86bca560ddf7906d43c0fcf80dd331163a22ea3e

commit_message:
Add support for "signals" to os-refresh-config

The new software config / deployments resources use signals.

A subtle difference between wait condition handles and signals in Heat
is that signals use POST, but wait conditions use PUT. This has
historical reasons that mostly are due to Amazon compatibility. We need
to continue to support both until we can eliminate all use of wait
conditions.

Change-Id: I69d9103b07100f700fb71a2cbbf267042625e7a7

[{'created': '2014-04-09 01:29:05.000000000', 'message': 'NSX: Fix KeyError in sync if nsx_router_id not found

Previously, a KeyError would occur in the sync code which would
cause the sync thread to stop running. This would occur if there
was a router entry in the database but no nsx_router_mapping and
the router was not found in nsx. Note: this should never happen unless
one did not run the db migration which introduced and migrated the data
for the NeutronNsxRouterMapping table.

(cherry picked from commit d90d71cfdae1d9c9c3b54cc33adfabce683c633c)
Change-Id: I44f3e7de9323f594501db63d3ad33e80e617bfdc
Closes-bug: #1304647
'}]
commit_message:
NSX: Fix KeyError in sync if nsx_router_id not found

Previously, a KeyError would occur in the sync code which would
cause the sync thread to stop running. This would occur if there
was a router entry in the database but no nsx_router_mapping and
the router was not found in nsx. Note: this should never happen unless
one did not run the db migration which introduced and migrated the data
for the NeutronNsxRouterMapping table.

(cherry picked from commit d90d71cfdae1d9c9c3b54cc33adfabce683c633c)
Change-Id: I44f3e7de9323f594501db63d3ad33e80e617bfdc
Closes-bug: #1304647

commit_message:
Add service-delete subcommand to delete a service

In nova https://review.openstack.org/#/c/39998/ expose an API to delete
a service. Both in V1.1 and V3.

This patch make novaclient support it.

Change-Id: I4aaabc866b464c046b46eda68734f37223c6d6a0
Implements: blueprint support-delete-service

commit_message:
Fix anti-affinity server-group boot failure

When the second instance is booted to an anti-affinity group
the scheduler fails with an exception due to a missing type conversion.

Closes-Bug: #1301982
Change-Id: I87b2a8d8c7d04b781c789374d6e9c7f4c8567e5d
(cherry picked from commit 1680cf8cef9bd670306a0ef74803409f60f21f28)

commit_message:
Clean out namespaces even if we don't delete namespaces

Even when we don't enable namespace deletion, we still want to run the
code that cleans out the namespaces so that the devices get unplugged,
etc.  Otherwise, routers deleted while the agent is down will continue
to operate as if they were never deleted.

The trade-off to consider here is that if there are many stale
namespaces this will slow down the restart of the L3 agent.  The best
option is to get namespace deletion working correctly.  However, where
that has not been worked out yet, this patch provides the cleaning
service for deleted routers.

Change-Id: Ic7b4608a23c4d9530f521d5faff3f8526200b92e
Closes-Bug: #1301042
Related-Bug: #1052535

commit_message:
BSN: Remove module-level ref to httplib method

Removes a module-level variable that was just a
pointer to the httplib.HTTPConnection class. It's
purpose was to give mock.patch a target that wouldn't
affect other code using the httplib.HTTPConnection
library. However, it is unnecessary now that the
root cause of the original patches not being stopped
by mock.patch.stopall was fixed in bug 1303605 (change
Ia5b374c5f8d3a7905d915de4f1f8d4f3a6f0e58d).

Closes-Bug: #1304558
Change-Id: Idf814b075a80245bb9751466c2b58d719a1b81f3

in Cisco N1kv Plugin.

commit_message:
Move "Launch an Instance" to end of Install Guide

Moved the "Launch an Instance" section to the bottom of the
install guide, to prevent readers from having to jump around
from later chapters.  Also added a note at the end of every
chapter, starting with the Networking chapter, letting them
know that they can launch an instance or add additional
features.

Change-Id: Ie356370bb1a1efa28e36f8f2e25fdc3fff8b35d6
Implements: networking-install-guide-improvements
Closes-Bug: 1301180

commit_message:
Adds missing expected_errors for V3 API multinic extension

The V3 API multinic extension is missing the expected errors
decorators which means that unexpected internal Nova exceptions
are not caught correctly. This patch adds the expected error
decorators.

Change-Id: I99311275197bb5123079c8910855386252028dec
Closes-Bug: 1303781

commit_message:
Enable ServerGroup scheduler filters by default

The Icehouse release includes a server group REST API. For these
groups to actually function properly, the server group scheduler
filters must be enabled. So, these filters should be enabled by
default since the API is also enabled by default. If the API is not
used, the scheduler filters will be a no-op.

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ia52d7fcfff52377d8beae2acd9b7eba9c6c74e09
Closes-bug: #1303983
(cherry picked from commit 7b8402ed3ba734836119441bdf1a6d6c661c8df2)

commit_message:
add tests for extension: os-extended-volume

this add tests for extension: os-extended-volume.
also add an parameter in xml_to_json in order to we can some
xml element that should be transferred to the type: list.
like the following case:
<os-extended-volumes:volume_attached id="c524a65f-164a-4677-a051-b80022b41e8c"/>
<os-extended-volumes:volume_attached id="c68a8540-05dd-4abd-a689-f02ddd029a23"/>
should be transferred to:
volume_attached: [{"id": c524a65f-164a-4677-a051-b80022b41e8c},
                  {"id": c68a8540-05dd-4abd-a689-f02ddd029a23}]
currently it will be transferred to:
volume_attached: {"id": c68a8540-05dd-4abd-a689-f02ddd029a23}
the first volume id will be overridden.

this patch also addresses this issue by the way.

Change-Id: Ib1ca03ab7b693bf91de577b89707b265248cdffb

commit_message:
add tests for server detail and show with extensions

this adds the tests for server detail and show action with
the following extensions:
keypair
config_drive
extended_availability_zone
extend_status
extended_server_attributes

*this also remove the _host_key in test_aggregates.py for xml test,
it needn't be handled specially now.

Change-Id: I3ecaca5a64dcdd5ff8dc3f2d18f7ca58ac04395d

commit_message:
Add safe_resize2fs to be public

Moves safe_resize2fs method outside the method extend
to be used as a public method of disk.api.

Related to blueprint libvirt-resize-disk-down

Change-Id: Id0a5b261abb5c5a247e27e60c6cb3936d866aa78

(1 inline comment)

Jay, if you look at the console.html files in the logs you'll see the formatting of the lines printed when the tests are run has changed. For example:

http://logs.openstack.org/21/70021/7/check/check-tempest-dsvm-full/6c6c984/console.html.gz#_2014-01-30_22_17_59_738

So for the -1, if we're going to stick with the tabs to delineate between workers (in the example above it only showed one worker, is that a bug in the new filter?) I think we definitely need to have a flag to enable that as the behavior. Or maybe switch between tabs and numbers like Robert originally had. My concern which I raised on IRC is that with more than a few workers the tabbing will be pretty crazy. While in the gate VMs 4 workers is probably our upper bound people do run tempest on (or against) real hardware and I think using tabs with more than 4 workers will get messy very quickly."}, {'account_id': 7, 'date': '2014-02-03 14:57:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

Thanks Matthew... actually took me a while to see what the difference was. I was looking for the " "*5 stuff, to see a kind of "hierarchical view" of the tests based on Sean's original request...

Anyway, so besides the timing appearing in the right place (yay!), I would love to see the hierarchical view of the tests, as well as a return of the test tags (e.g. gate, negative, smoke, etc). Robert, is there any way to add that in?

Best,

-jay'}, {'account_id': 4190, 'date': '2014-02-06 20:16:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

@Jay"""Anyway, so besides the timing appearing in the right place (yay!), I would love to see the hierarchical view of the tests, as well as a return of the test tags (e.g. gate, negative, smoke, etc). Robert, is there any way to add that in?"""

The gate/etc stuff aren't subunit stream tags [at the moment] - they affect the test id and should still be listed unless Sean has added code to strip them :).

Not sure what you mean by hierarchical - if you mean grouping by class - well we could infer that from the ids, but the concurrent nature of this prohibits that - we're specifically interested in making analysis visually easier.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-06 20:16:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: No score

commit_message:
Add in a concurrency aware subunit filter

A live filter for subunit stream that will let us display the
concurrency of the streams as we go.

This includes a visual offset filter, which makes it very
quick to see execution in the workers.

Co-Authored-By: Robert Collins <rbtcollins@hp.com>

Change-Id: I1b529546e005f47aba56b451e1c0d8b0da09fca3

Change-Id: I9b7c13e166d98c75f3cad1bf92c23a13a06557fd
Implements: blueprint refactor-database-app-guest-functionality
"}]
commit_message:
Refactor mysql and redis apps

Reasons:
 - each time mysql and redis manager and
   backup/restore strategies instantiate
   mysql/redis app object. This is not
   correct since mysql app doesn't change
   while guest is working.

Changes:
 - app refactoring;
 - tests refactoring;

Change-Id: I9b7c13e166d98c75f3cad1bf92c23a13a06557fd
Implements: blueprint refactor-database-app-guest-functionality

commit_message:
Add hidden attribute to output params in HOT DSL

This would allow for controlling the display/providing of sensitive
information in the outputs section.

The use case of hidden outputs:
  A user defines outputs in the template that includes sensitive data,
  such as username/password information, that I don't necessarily
  want displayed at all times, similar to how template parameters can
  be hidden.
  E.g.: I may not be in a safe environment to have that information in
  the open.

Co-Authored-By: Anderson Mesquita <andersonvom@gmail.com>
Implements: blueprint add-hidden-attribute-to-outputs
Change-Id: I7755aeef8a9b1e9b6ee4ec200f17e5e05b8d701d

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-04-01 11:28:07.000000000', 'message': "Use cwd for lock_path(directory) if directory is empty

lock_path(directory) fails if the directory is ''. This happens for
example if one is using swift-account-info on a database in the
current directory; in that case os.path.dirname() returns ''.

This patch replaces an empty directory name with os.getcwd() and
adds a verifying unit test.

Fixes-Bug: 1300721
Change-Id: Ibcb6475138e83aa558163e273b0ce11109f13515
"}]
commit_message:
Use cwd for lock_path(directory) if directory is empty

lock_path(directory) fails if the directory is ''. This happens for
example if one is using swift-account-info on a database in the
current directory; in that case os.path.dirname() returns ''.

This patch replaces an empty directory name with os.getcwd() and
adds a verifying unit test.

Fixes-Bug: 1300721
Change-Id: Ibcb6475138e83aa558163e273b0ce11109f13515

commit_message:
Add a message to update notifications

Add a human readable message to compute instance notifications.  This
will make it easier for notification consumers to deduce the purpose of
the update.

Change-Id: Ib1cf9219056e9052e3b62d05d884e306e707d0df
Implements: blueprint message-in-update-notifications

commit_message:
Ensure network interfaces are in requested order

_build_network_info_model was iterating current_neutron_ports
instead of port_ids which contains ports in their correctly requested
order. Because of this the requested nic order was no longer being
perserved. This patch fixes this and also changes the order of ports
in test_build_network_info_model() so this case is tested.

Closes-bug: #1300325

Conflicts:

	nova/network/neutronv2/api.py
	nova/tests/network/test_neutronv2.py

Change-Id: Ia9e71364bca6cbc24ebc1c234e6a5af14f51cd62
(cherry picked from commit 720e7f939859fbfe6b0c79ef3a6d5e43c916da65)

commit_message:
Load user un-lazily if needed

Add a keystone lookup if the user is not found in class cache.
This can happen if a user is created after prefetching.
Forcing a lookup and refreshing cache fix this issue.

Change-Id: I8c74d955539c224f82755fb6b29a9fa562ad8959

commit_message:
Bootstrap 2 to Bootstrap 3 update

This draft is for lesscpy debug puposes as lesscpy is not able to succesfully compile the bootstrap 3
and horizon.less as it does not support all required Less features.

Initial bootstrap files update: updated less, fonts and js bootstrap files, removed bootstrap images
Replaced old variables with new in horizon.less
Renamed row-fluid class to row
Replaced grid span class with col-md- class
New icon classes and put icons into span element where possible
New button classes
Removed button icons in favour of upcoming font-icons blueprint
Added bootstrap overrides less structure to enable clean overriding of bootstrap features
Fixed dropdowns
Tables overrides, tweaks
Fixed messages
Updated modals templates, js, styling to work with new bootstrap 3 modals
Updated forms using django-bootstrap-forms, alerts, tooltips and form validation messages, data-add-item select fix
Membership widget update
Table head fixes, tenant switcher fix, sidebar navtabs fix, fix tabgroup clearing, datepicker fixes,
workflow footer buttons fix, cancel button fix, make primary submit button smaller, fix modal scrolling issue
with dropdown_fix

Implements: blueprint bootstrap-update

Change-Id: I225246b9f8f27cd8c653ec777390686c36b01b90

I have the impression that we have a regression on buttons with glyphicons (btn-download, btn-upload, btn-launch, etc...), there is no solution for this on bootstrap v3?

Thanks for a review!

I have used django-bootstrap-form because bootstrap 3 uses bootstrap-related classes directly on input elements. django-bootstrap-form identifies the type of input element and adds required bootstrap classes to these django widgets. I think it is better approach then adding class manually to each input definition in django. Other way to do it would be creating our own django widgets, but that's what we get from django-bootstrap-form. Maybe there is another option I don't know of?

I have the impression that we have a regression on buttons with glyphicons (btn-download, btn-upload, btn-launch, etc...), there is no solution for this on bootstrap v3?
I also think we need to reintegrate the lessc compiler, lesscpy does not provide as many pros to avoid the cons we encountered every time we try to use less.

I have removed the button icons on purpose as bootstrap 3 uses font icons now, and it identifies the icons differently. Re-enabling icons is identified as separate blueprint, that depends on this one, to reduce the ammount of code changed in this already large patch. commit_message:
Upgrade bootstrap 2 to bootstrap 3

This draft is for the review purposes, it includes revert to lessc library
as only that is able to succesfully compile bootstrap 3

Enable back lessc:
Revert "Drop NodeJS dependency in favor of pure-python lesscpy"
This reverts commit a0739c9423a4c559b45af96fa4cdb30539dcdbd7.
Update lessc library in horizon

Initial bootstrap files update: updated less, fonts and js bootstrap files, removed bootstrap images
Replaced old variables with new in horizon.less
Renamed row-fluid class to row
Replaced grid span class with col-md- class
New icon classes and put icons into span element where possible
New button classes
Removed button icons in favour of upcoming font-icons blueprint
Added bootstrap overrides less structure to enable clean overriding of bootstrap features
Fixed dropdowns
Tables overrides, tweaks
Fixed messages
Updated modals templates, js, styling to work with new bootstrap 3 modals
Updated forms using django-bootstrap-forms, alerts, tooltips and form validation messages, data-add-item select fix
Membership widget update
Table head fixes, tenant switcher fix, sidebar navtabs fix, fix tabgroup clearing, datepicker fixes,
workflow footer buttons fix, cancel button fix, make primary submit button smaller, fix modal scrolling issue
with dropdown_fix

Implements: blueprint bootstrap-update

Change-Id: I5324038756ba98c59d3db0b0d2cd4c14c5c8be9c

Are you concerned about the performance impact of udev settle? It should not matter.

Thinking about it though, I tend to say that waiting for udev is a good thing in both cases. The part I don't quite get is why/whether udevadm settle is really needed.  Is it udev that's interfering or something else?

Presumably lvchange does something related to this by default since it has a "--noudevsync" option described as "Disable udev synchronisation. The process will not wait for notification from udev." ?'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2014-01-31 19:11:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

Comments inline, I'm definitely NOT in favor of removing udev settle, but I would prefer the logic to be inline with the code you're replacing.  This was a serious bug that we fixed, RHEL as I understand it has some different mechanisms that it has implemented that don't exist on other platforms so it probably never actually hits this case as we have it coded today.

The settle however is still the "universal" version and it was only turned off in the default implementation of the LVM driver because it can be slow sometimes and cause issues for systems booting off of LVM (if I remember all of this correctly).'}, {'account_id': 4523, 'date': '2014-02-03 21:59:19.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Nothing I am talking about here is specific to RHEL.  I don't understand how having to run udevadm settle matches with what shows up in lvm.conf (on Ubuntu or RHEL or wherever) that says

activation {

  # Set to 0 to disable udev synchronisation (if compiled 
into the binaries).
  ...

    udev_sync = 1


Maybe this is not the right thing but it seems like we need to understand the mechanics of this udev call.  (Or, I'd like to at least.)"}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2014-02-11 06:03:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Abandoned

commit_message:
Deactivate LV before removing

With certain versions of LVM2, removing an active LV can end up with

  Unable to deactivate open XXX
  libdevmapper exiting with 1 device(s) still suspended.

which causes any lvm command afterwards to hang endlessly on
trying to access the suspended volume. This seems to be caused
by a race with udev, so lets be conservative and do the deactivation,
then wait for udev and then finish the removal.

Closes-Bug: #1270192

Change-Id: I4703133180567090878ea5047dd29d9f97ad85ab

commit_message:
Sync oslo imageutils, strutils to Nova

Changes in imageutils:
===============================
b455fac Enable decimal value input in imageutils.QemuImgInfo
bec3a5e Implements SI/IEC unit system conversion to bytes
8b2b0b7 Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._
aad179d Fixing misspelled encryption key in QemuImgInfo
12bcdb7 Remove vim header
2bd46eb Refactors byte size extraction logic

Changes in strutils:
====================
bec3a5e Implements SI/IEC unit system conversion to bytes
e53fe85 strutils bool_from_string, allow specified default
8b2b0b7 Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._
84d461e Fix a bug in safe_encode where it returns a bytes object in py3
12bcdb7 Remove vim header
3970d46 Fix typos in oslo
1a2df89 Enable H302 hacking check
67bd769 python3: Fix traceback while running python3.
b0c51ec Refactors to_bytes

Change-Id: I3e887756af37823dc6486d1496222825ddc20f0c
Related-bug: #1189635
Related-bug: #1193765
Related-Bug: #1257829

commit_message:
Add common base class for agent functional tests

Refactor the functional tests a bit to add a common base class for agent
tests. This is needed an upcoming commit which adds a functional test
for VXLAN version checking.

Closes-Bug: #1301363

Change-Id: I438e401cbfb40e5557e5125f2a409bac5c1fd1c2

commit_message:
NSX: Fix KeyError in sync if nsx_router_id not found

Previously, a KeyError would occur in the sync code which would
cause the sync thread to stop running. This would occur if there
was a router entry in the database but no nsx_router_mapping and
the router was not found in nsx. Note: this should never happen unless
one did not run the db migration which introduced and migrated the data
for the NeutronNsxRouterMapping table.

Change-Id: I44f3e7de9323f594501db63d3ad33e80e617bfdc
Closes-bug: #1304647

commit_message:
Add configurable ovsdb monitor respawn interval

If minimize_polling=True and the ovsdb-client process died, the
default respawn interval of 0 would mean that we'd start polling
again. This patch adds the option ovsdb_monitor_respawn_interval and
defaults it to 30 seconds.

Change-Id: I12c1e05ec4d6d2bd4d84024a91116e2ac3974868
Close-Bug: 1243867
(cherry picked from commit 14950e492ad4423aa6f8719f7178b0477294ba5a)

commit_message:
Verify the response attributes of 'aggregate-set-metadata' API

This patch verifies the response attributes of 'aggregate-set-metadata'.
The response attributes of v2 and v3 are the same:
{
    "aggregate": {
        "availability_zone": "nova",
        "created_at": "2012-11-16T06:22:22.342791",
        "deleted": false,
        "deleted_at": null,
        "hosts": [],
        "id": 1,
        "metadata": {
            "availability_zone": "nova",
            "key": "value"
        },
        "name": "name",
        "updated_at": null
    }
}

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I8940a18e71540aec300023e6736a3318b253d702

commit_message:
Hide ipv6 subnet API attributes

The attributes for ra mode and address mode should be hidden
until the IPv6 feature is fully implemented.

The changes in this patch will be reverted by another patch
which closes this bug.

Change-Id: I69a1a571b5beb566641200e60b84f0716c1ec138
Related-Bug: 1304093
(cherry picked from commit d739486a3f70cb83f8730cf7201a8b8ccf4b4c70)

commit_message:
auth_token middleware hashes tokens with sha256

The auth_token middleware always hashed PKI Tokens with MD5. This
change makes it so that PKI tokens can be hashed with SHA256. This
is for security hardening.

Both SHA256 and MD5 will be tried when checking against the
revocation list. This will support identity servers that are not
configured for SHA256.

When storing the PKI token in the local cache, the sha256 hash will
always be used.

SecurityImpact
Closes-Bug: #1174499

Change-Id: I9fe61354103b59dfd292740fbec35e9c6f5ef765

commit_message:
Hide ipv6 subnet API attributes

The attributes for ra mode and address mode should be hidden
until the IPv6 feature is fully implemented.

The changes in this patch will be reverted by another patch
which closes this bug.

Change-Id: I69a1a571b5beb566641200e60b84f0716c1ec138
Related-Bug: 1304093

commit_message:
Fix Jenkins translation jobs

The -propose-translation-update and -upstream-translation-update
jobs do not update from transifex since our po files contain
duplicate entries where obsolete entries duplicate normal entries.

Remove all obsolete entries to fix the jobs.

Change-Id: Ia174a145e71ab6c2bfd99f06e8ebead2e91e15ea
Closes-Bug: #1299349

commit_message:
Check top-level sections when parsing a template

This patch adds validation to template parsing to detect any sections
that do not comply with allowed sections in a template. In the past,
there have been cases where small typos in section names (e.g.
'output' instead of 'outputs') did not get detected and caused issues
at a later point, i.e. by simply not showing any stack outputs.

The place where the template.validate() call has been added to the
parser code only affects new stacks and rejects invalid templates
with an error message. This does not affect stacks that are already
in the database (I did some tests to check this).

Change-Id: Ifed4207badeb364675c905224ba762a9d8eaedd9
Closes-Bug: #1297761

commit_message:
Fix timeout for stack actions

The problem is that the timeout for running any action (i.e. create or update)
on stack is not passed from parent stack to nested stack.
All heat resources which are internally implemented as StackResource are
affected. For example AutoScalingGroup always using default timeout
(60 minutes). If creating any of the instances will take more that it will
fail no matter what timeout you will pass creating stack.

Changes:
* removes hardcoded timeout (60 minutes)
* adds new config option to specify timeout for stack action
* if timeout was not specified for nested stack then timeout from parent
  is used
* adds test for StackResource and parser.Stack

Change-Id: I39494b75774988c625cb22cc7873d628c04d3228
Closes-Bug: 1287719

[{'created': '2014-04-08 20:41:49.000000000', 'message': 'Correctly inherit __table_args__ from parent class

Where unique constraints are added to certain tables by populating
__table_args__, we need to ensure we inherit the top level
__table_args__ that define the default storage engine to use when
creating tables.

Change-Id: Ib886b84922830b60282b4f882591e43f5041e713
Fixes: bug 1288358
(cherry picked from commit 72e37ddcd067432675543c8f4d327fe766bc8044)
'}]
commit_message:
Correctly inherit __table_args__ from parent class

Where unique constraints are added to certain tables by populating
__table_args__, we need to ensure we inherit the top level
__table_args__ that define the default storage engine to use when
creating tables.

Change-Id: Ib886b84922830b60282b4f882591e43f5041e713
Fixes: bug 1288358
(cherry picked from commit 72e37ddcd067432675543c8f4d327fe766bc8044)

[{'created': '2014-04-04 19:30:41.000000000', 'message': 'Attempt to ensure connect always timesout

It seems that the test_connect_put_timeout() test does not always fail
when it is expected. Sometimes, not very often, the attempt to connect
succeeds, resulting in a failed test.

This might be because the fake-connection infrastructure uses a
sleep(0.1) and the test uses a connect timeout of 0.1. There might be a
case where the two values result in the exact time where the entries
happen to be added in the wrong order such that the sleep() completes
first before the connect timeout fires, where the connect completes
successfully.

Closes bug 1302781

Change-Id: Ie23e40cf294170eccdf0713e313f9a31a92f9071
'}]
commit_message:
Attempt to ensure connect always timesout

It seems that the test_connect_put_timeout() test does not always fail
when it is expected. Sometimes, not very often, the attempt to connect
succeeds, resulting in a failed test.

This might be because the fake-connection infrastructure uses a
sleep(0.1) and the test uses a connect timeout of 0.1. There might be a
case where the two values result in the exact time where the entries
happen to be added in the wrong order such that the sleep() completes
first before the connect timeout fires, where the connect completes
successfully.

Closes bug 1302781

Change-Id: Ie23e40cf294170eccdf0713e313f9a31a92f9071

commit_message:
update setup.py with pbr version

This file is normally updated in the standard "update from
global requirements" patch, but since those contain other
changes we don't want, the setup.py file never gets updated.

This patch updates setup.py to bring it in line with the
standard global requirements way of doing things without also
updating [test-]requirements.txt

Change-Id: Id0e4f8e17dd4c714b4d2dd75985431a9e12e6a4f

commit_message:
Cherry pick oslo-incubator db fixes

The patch cherrypicks 2 fixes related to utf8 migration:

 * Ib5c0f93c788afda92aad862e50dc086dc39605f1: Ignore migrate versioning tables in utf8 sanity check

 * I7f271d846141ac72dde3fb0d12159b125018eb2c: Make table utf-8 charset checking be optional for DB migration

Change-Id: Icb811e846c05f863a42611054f2e3f30a47573db
Closes-Bug: #1301036

Jordan, thanks for the review. Do you mean move read CONF logic into "def create_volume(self, size, **kwargs)" of volumes_client.py instead of in the testcase that call this method? I'm thinking of 2 plans. First:
def create_volume(self, size, **kwargs):
    size = CONF.volume.volume_size
Second:
def create_volume(self, **kwargs):
    size = CONF.volume.volume_size

First is keep to paramter but ignore it, read CONF everytime when create volume. 
Second is remove the size parameter and modify all the service consumer, but it would be too much impact to change in this bug. I see totally 10 places to fix.

I still have concern that size is parater for each caller to specify, it might different size by caller for different reason. Is it proper to specify the same size to create all the volume? Thanks.'}, {'account_id': 7350, 'date': '2014-03-26 14:43:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

>Do you mean move read CONF logic into "def create_volume(self, size, **kwargs)" of volumes_client.py instead of in the testcase that call this method? 
Exactly.

In fact, I was thinking of a third option :)
def create_volume(self, size=None, **kwargs):
    if not size:
      size = CONF.volume.volume_size

There's even a fourth option
def create_volume(self, size, **kwargs):
  if 'imageRef' in kwargs and kwargs.get('imageRef'):
    size = CONF.compute.image_size

I think we should wait for other comments and especially Matthew's opinion.'}, {'account_id': 5196, 'date': '2014-03-26 14:59:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

So Jordon's first method listed in his most recent comment is the best way to do this. It should be specifying a default volume creation size. Defaulting to a hardcoded value will just cause issues. (in probably more than just the image case too)

So the best option is to make the default create size configurable. That way if you're using an image larger than 1 GB you can change the default volume create size to match it. The image size for whatever imageref is should be independent from what the default volume create size is. It also doesn't need to be specified in the config file because if we need that info for a test we can just query glance to grab it."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-03-26 15:26:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Works for me

Zhi Kun Liu, per discussion with Jordan and Matthew above. We'd like to fix this as modifying the 
"create_volume(self, size, **kargs)" to

[{'created': '2014-03-19 08:00:10.000000000', 'message': "Fix the tempest case, when create a volume with imageRef set, also
need set the size={image_size} rather than the hardcode 1G.

This change determines by if the imageRef passed, if so get image
detail info from images_client, and get image size from
'OS-EXT-IMG-SIZE:size' property, then parse it to gigabit unit.
If no imageRef passed in, create volume with the default 1G size.

commit_message:
Volume size could be specified to create volume

1. Provide a "volume_size" config at VolumeGroup
2. Make size as optional prameter, modify all volumes_client to
read the size from CONf if size is None.
3. Modify the testcase: test_volume_create_get_update
_delete_from_image to call create_volume with no size
parameter specified.

Change-Id: I2897f6d6bd970f73867f56d9d23a768cafcbfd80
Closes-Bug: #1293885

Thanks for the comments, will address shortly.

@Masayuki--RE: the current ironic tests and whether we'd skip this exercise--yes thats intentional.  The current check deploys devstack in a typical nova+libvirt/kvm setup, but also deploys the ironic API and conductor services.  The API tests in tempest right now conduct some simple CRUD tests against that API.  That can happen with or without the Ironic compute driver enabled.

This adds the driver_enabled flag that we can use to trigger the proposed scenario test when Ironic is deployed AND nova-compute is configured to use the Ironic driver.  This is the case in the experimental check-tempest-dsvm-virtual-ironic job. commit_message:
Adds Ironic test_baremetal_basic_ops scenario test

Adds an Ironic scenario test that validates a full instance
boot using Ironic.  In addition to verifying the Nova instance
boots and has connectivity, it monitors power and state transitions
on the Ironic side.  It currently validates orchestration of the pxe_ssh
driver but the goal would be to support other drivers, and test them
conditionally based on the driver associated with the configured Ironic
node.

Change-Id: I7a98ab9c771fe17387dfb591df5a40d27194a5c8

commit_message:
Update percona xtradb-cluster package

It appears that percona no longer offers a binary with static linked
ssl. Updating the download URL and symlink hacks to work with new
package.

Closes-Bug: #1304629
Change-Id: I0563375c46bd4dcc2b704128ddc742ec11bb6459

This patch does the same for *update* operations as well.'}, {'account_id': 1689, 'date': '2014-04-04 03:08:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Mohammad,

Thanks for the clarification. Not sure why I said "delete". Was thinking about drivers that track port binding state, and need to see all operations, including update and delete. 

-Bob'}, {'account_id': 6558, 'date': '2014-04-04 07:13:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I am in principal agreement with this fix and like it. 

However, I am giving -1 to ensure that everybody is aware of the fact that this creates an issue, if the MDs are inter-dependent upon each other and are using the order of the MD execution to deal with this interdependency. 
So, in such a case, if one MD fails, the next will fail as well, because it was dependent upon the previous MD's execution. 

This fix is good if we assume that MDs must not be inter-dependent. In general I would assume they are not....but, in absence of any such documentation, it is worthwhile to bring it out here.

-Sukhdev"}, {'account_id': 6558, 'date': '2014-04-05 17:44:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

I am reversing my -1 vote for the following reason: 

As I mentioned earlier, I like the fix, but, was hesitant because of inter-dependence issue of the MDs- i.e. one MD may be dependent upon the work done by other MD.  

Considering the fact that we do not have any documentation giving clear guidelines as to how the inter-dependence be handled, and moreover, ML2 Plugin does not explicitly  guarantee any sequence other than the fact the MDs are invoked in certain order. Invocation of the MDs in certain order does not really guarantee that the back-end work have been successfully completed by a given MD. Therefore, any MD which is using this ordered invocation to imply the inter-dependence are really going beyond the guidelines/guarantee of ML2 Plugin.  

Hence, I believe we should merge this fix ASAP and see if there are offenders. The only way to catch the offenders will be by merging this fix. If we see such inter-dependence cases, then we will address them in a more concrete and formal manner. 

if rest of you agree with my rationale, lets please get this approved and get into Icehouse-RC2. 

Thanks
-Sukhdev'}, {'account_id': 2888, 'date': '2014-04-07 08:04:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

commit_message:
Deals with fails in update_*_postcommit ops

It makes all mechanism drivers called even when one
of the mechanism drivers fails during a post commit
operation for updating network/subnet/port. This is
a stopgap measure until a more comprehensive approach
is adopted and implemented.

Change-Id: Ia9080a91ce768d4007b0525548acfe7443a2973c
Partial-Bug: 1227336

commit_message:
Don't specify admin_token in paste config

This is not a value that is going to be useful on other systems and
shouldn't be included in the default pipeline.

Closes-Bug: #1299332

commit_message:
Credentials for native heat os-collect-config polling

For Server software_config_transport=POLL_SERVER_HEAT the os-collect-config
configuration has been changed in the following way:
* included stack_id and resource_name
* replaced username with user_id, since domain users should always be
  referenced by ID.
* renamed the collector key from "heat_server_poll" to "heat" since that
  is the intended name for the heat collector in os-collect-config

Closes-Bug: #1299986

Change-Id: I42326c81c7276d7d305a05c00d72a6102e80abca

commit_message:
Allow for stack users in _authorize_stack_user

This change allows stack user credentials to be used to call
describe_stack_resource (heat resource-metadata)

It makes the following changes:
* _authorize_stack_user first attempts authorize with
  stack.access_allowed using the context user_id before falling back
  to looking for ec2 credentials
* context middleware sets the user_id on the context even when the
  username is not specified

This change also adds missing test coverage to ContextMiddleware

Change-Id: Idb655e403ba11a3144dacf34eba0feb59ab8d911
Closes-Bug: #1299982

[{'created': '2014-03-18 06:08:59.000000000', 'message': 'define ceph::key.

Provides keyring management.

Handles cephkeys (cephx), creating keyring files, injecting keys into
the keyring via ceph and ceph-autotool tools. Includes support for
multiple keys in the same keyring file (as this is supported by the
ceph-authtool tool).

Includes rspec system puppet for validation.

Change-Id: Ib3c4832ffcff61ab42ae221cdd5a5bfb76ee36c5
Implements: blueprint puppet-ceph#key

commit_message:
define ceph::key.

Provides keyring management.

Handles cephkeys (cephx), creating keyring files, injecting keys into
the keyring via ceph and ceph-autotool tools. Includes support for
multiple keys in the same keyring file (as this is supported by the
ceph-authtool tool).

Includes rspec system puppet for validation.

Change-Id: Ib3c4832ffcff61ab42ae221cdd5a5bfb76ee36c5
Implements: blueprint puppet-ceph#key

commit_message:
Fix Jenkins translation jobs

The jobs heat-propose-translation-update and
heat-upstream-translation-update do not update from
transifex since our po files contain duplicate entries where
obsolete entries duplicate normal entries.

Remove all obsolete entries to fix the jobs.

Change-Id: I2071e3a792d107840449bbfe39e3a540ea1b626f
Closes-Bug: #1299349

commit_message:
Add a resource_facade intrinsic function to HOT

Add a native version of the function, rather than continue to rely on
Fn::ResourceFacade from the Heat-flavoured-cfn templates.

Closes-bug: #1299205

Change-Id: Iee118aeaa72d59e4d6a27ed487b99e9aba9779cd

commit_message:
Resolve data from Resource Facade

Since we are looking directly at the template data for the resource facade,
we need to resolve any intrinsic functions that may be present. (For
example, this would be expected if we ever had more than one level of
provider templates, or if e.g. the DeletionPolicy was passed as parameter
to the main stack).

Closes-bug: #1299204

Change-Id: Iaae2fe7be6618c1dee84f2c90bdc179dc2be67d6

commit_message:
Add configurable handler selection for Deployer

Added to solum-deployer the configuration value 'handler'
to select which one of the available modules in its
handlers directory to use as its endpoint. The result is
being able to configure exactly how images will be deployed.

At present we only have default.py, which uses Heat to deploy
a stack for the app, but in the future there may be other
handlers to use another process.

Since default.py was using Heat, I renamed it to heat.py and
added a new default.py mainly for contract enforcement.

Change-Id: I4c2aefc7d60e421c176bb8e854548486e9d800a3

commit_message:
Add a default DeletionPolicy for Fn::ResourceFacade

The provider template can't know whether this is explicitly included in the
facade resource's definition, and shouldn't need to.

Closes-bug: #1299202

Change-Id: I01177a84b86b69e221d83d87f3efd9e07e5b9c1f

commit_message:
Always answer empty list if deployments not ready

An empty deployments will cause json decode exception, and once
deployments=[] coming, it will trigger another refresh. Always answer
empty list when deployments not ready will solve above two issues.

Change-Id: Iaee3a3ef25cf9907aaefd941dcb316ecb25a29d6
Closes-Bug: #1298417

commit_message:
Ensure parameter timeout_mins available in update

The parameter timeout_mins is not available when
updating a stack. The updater gets it from the
old stack no matter whether timeout_mins is
offered or not.

If timeout_mins is not offered in the new stack,
get the timeout from the old stack, and update
this parameter using the new stack's timeout.

Change-Id: I7d04d0f0b7cc917d49d45c0d3e1d5a8ffb7bff0b
Closes-Bug: 1290603

commit_message:
Insertion port id in address attribute of server

Dictionary returned by server's attribute addresses does not contain
port id value. Current patch adds field port in this dictionary.

Change-Id: Ie458e67d976af0dd394c3fa4a6d77bce78161bef
Closes-bug: #1285899

commit_message:
Allow passing auth plugin as a parameter

This further separates the concept of session and auth plugin so that
the session can be a completely standalone transport layer.

This is similar to how requests handles things. You can install an auth
plugin on the session object and then everything that works through the
session will be authenticated or you can specify the auth plugin per
request and only authenticate that request.

Change-Id: If4ed5af831cc35e259d9f963062261819f08a9d5

commit_message:
Add L2 Agent side handling for non consistent security_group settings

Add setting of the firewall_driver to NoopDriver when firewall_driver is None and
add warning if driver combination is not valid.
Modify is_valid_driver_combination to verify default settings: enable_security_group (True) and firewall_driver (None).

Change-Id: I841f9cf96ac6ee2ad17a4e8908d6c8a96f368cca
Closes-Bug: #1296957
(cherry picked from commit 5c6ff449bbd7386f0f3e41efc524024434f325df)

commit_message:
Fix deprecation warning

Accessing BaseException.message spews a warning; we can get the same
information with str(err), which does not spew.

Change-Id: I67648d53d25522be074a78c44b3ce97dc27d1f07

[{'created': '2014-04-07 08:22:23.000000000', 'message': "Catch loading failures if transport_url is not set

The current implementation always tries to get a transport from
oslo.messaging assuming the transport_url option has been set. This is
done to keep backwards compatibility. However, since the default
`rpc_backend` is rabbit, it'll always try to load such driver. The
problem raises when `kombu` is not installed and the `notifier_strategy`
is set to qpid. This will make glance-api fail because it'll try to load

"}]
commit_message:
Catch loading failures if transport_url is not set

The current implementation always tries to get a transport from
oslo.messaging assuming the transport_url option has been set. This is
done to keep backwards compatibility. However, since the default
`rpc_backend` is rabbit, it'll always try to load such driver. The
problem raises when `kombu` is not installed and the `notifier_strategy`
is set to qpid. This will make glance-api fail because it'll try to load
the rabbit driver *before* loading the qpid one.

This patch puts the first load attempt in a try / except block. The
error caught (if any) will be re-raised *just* if transport_url has been
configured, otherwise it'll move forward and try to load the notifier
driver using the old configuration options.

The patch also removes an obsolete test.

Change-Id: I00e653704463ea8245e2960050e0d5e6839f278a
Closes-bug: #1302661
(cherry picked from commit 164d1ab46f06141e2c12b944e15ae10f20dace38)

already pinned by hacking. This is the same way its done for all other
integrated projects.

commit_message:
Use a suffix in environment files

Rename environment files used by some openshift templates to have a
suffix so that they are more discoverable.

Change-Id: I99cf308e3fe18582f348d8e03f1407f00afb7f33

commit_message:
Adds TaskStub class

Partial Task patch, Id I4fbadc9a97e3147128c7c733384c7bb50918806f
removed the result and message vars of the Tasks class. However,
the succeed and fail methods were using those to update them
respectively. This patch introduces a new TaskStub class which
enables the PartialTask functionality without looking result
and message attrs of the Task class.

Fixes bug 1284975

Change-Id: I0b406e4662cfd3cb496b71be77ad10a90c178baa

commit_message:
node-list to show the maintenance field

The review https://review.openstack.org/#/c/84685/ added the maintenance
field from nodes to be shown in the GET /nodes. This patchs makes the
necessary changes to the CLI to reflect the changes in Ironic.

Change-Id: Iffb639f1e995ef73a5bda6dd3961a13ba5d865d0

commit_message:
Fixes versioning function tests with non-zero default policy

In each PUT, proxy-server will do HEAD request for container sync
and checking the object versions. This patch makes proxy-server
knows the non-zero default policy when HEADing

Change-Id: I29c5715a9dbc11d9f2ca9ccdfa7655beadf354f8

commit_message:
OFA agent: use hexadecimal IP address in tunnel port name

The remote IP address is used to form the tunnel port name
With some OVS/Linux combinations there is a 15 character limit
on port names, so a name like 'gre-192.168.10.10' does not work.
This fix uses the shorter hexadecimal representation of
the IP address instead.
This problem was reported and fixed for OVS agent.

Closes-Bug: 1294474

Change-Id: Ieab1eb8a5c430f69aff61a317cc28f23ba95ad2d

commit_message:
Correctly inherit __table_args__ from parent class

Where unique constraints are added to certain tables by populating
__table_args__, we need to ensure we inherit the top level
__table_args__ that define the default storage engine to use when
creating tables.

Change-Id: Ib886b84922830b60282b4f882591e43f5041e713
Fixes: bug 1288358

So I think the problem can't just be resolved by suppressing the error.  I think this is highlighting that we need to think harder about the containers table migration.  I added a test that pre-creates a row in the old containers schema - and it doesn't blow up, but I think the test shows other issues.

 1) we can't just alter the table and stuff in default values with an update, so I don't know what value the current existing containers are getting - but we should check - and we probably want to find a way to make it look and feel like a 0
 2) do we ever SELECT that column?  It seems to mainly be there for the triggers?  Shouldn't we want it in the containers iter?
 3) how can we back fill the policy_stats for existing containers?  Can we fire the triggers for the rows (maybe re-insert them with the right storage policy)?  Can we just duplicate the current account_stat bytes/count values into the policy_stats table since we know the cumulative values is the total?

Those maybe bigger problems that we should address separately, but either way I don't think there's much value in trying to squash it that way - let's just take out the UPDATE - it's not working anyway..."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-04-04 17:55:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Doesn't seem to work

'}, {'created': '2014-04-05 19:26:21.000000000', 'message': 'Fix issue with account broker and pre-SPI databases

When adding the spi column to the account database, we then
update the DB with spi 0 for that new column however if
a DB already existed this will trigger an existing check we
had to prevent such an action (UPDATE). To avoid this we
instead alter the table to setup an SPI column with a
DEFAULT SPI of 0 and then set the object_count and
byts_used for policy 0 in the policy_stat table to
their current values in the account_stat table which
correspond to the totals for policy 0 (existing stuff).

Change-Id: I6b3f591bad455dcd072056c28fc5a37c3f618e40
Implements: blueprint storage-policies

commit_message:
Fix issue with account broker and pre-SPI databases

Set a DEFAULT storage_policy_index for existing container rows during
migration.

Copy existing object_count and bytes_used in policy_stat table during
migration.

Change-Id: I6b3f591bad455dcd072056c28fc5a37c3f618e40
Implements: blueprint storage-policies

commit_message:
Include instance state in metadata

Instance state is missing from the resource
metadata. This fix includes the status of
an instance in resource/samples so its part
of the resource metadata.

Change-Id: I76edf1c3dabeb0d591d010d4b1771cdba6b95d36
Implements: blueprint ceilometer-instance-state-measurement

commit_message:
Inject all account details in tempest.conf

The tempest configuration function did not inject all account
details in tempest.conf. The only reason why it worked, was
because tempest uses default config values which are valid for
the current devstack setup.

To remove this dependency, two patches are needed:
- this one in devstack, to inject all values
- https://review.openstack.org/#/c/77602/ in tempest, to change
  default values to None

Partially fixes bug 1287191

Conflicts:
	lib/tempest

Change-Id: I01507b142703a1ff66707464b9a743e9d0ca3e01
(cherry picked from commit d46d9dd8de00d07eee9170365b1a025f0fc01ed9)

commit_message:
VMware: bug fix for VM rescue when config drive is configured

The addition of the config drive feature broke the VM rescue. The
cause of the problem was setting the instance UUID to the name of
the rescue instance. This must be a UUID! The solution
is to pass the instance name to the spawn method instead of writing
this on the instance UUID.

Closes-bug: #1247427

Conflicts:

	nova/virt/vmwareapi/vmops.py

Change-Id: Ia8494b0c8099753b666bda18a19c4c9a3f764616
(cherry picked from commit 88861df2b95a9c66a1a9d1969ad9e560786bb848)

commit_message:
Generate better bm network mac addresses for VMs

Previously we relied on libvirt to generate all of
our MAC addresses in configure-vms. This change
updates configure-vm so that we generate our
own inline MACs for the baremetal network (only)
such that the 2nd MSB bit is set high. (making
it so they aren't identified as locally administered).

This effectively allows our fake baremetal VMs to more
accurately behave like real hardware and fixes issues with
bridge/DHCP configurations which rely on the fact that bridges
assume the MAC address of the lowest attached NIC.

Change-Id: I052218d88b2d4362ad5eb99576e7064aee47863f

commit_message:
Add tests for remaining expected conductor exceptions

This fills out coverage of our expected exceptions on conductor
methods, which helps ensure we don't drop an expected exception
class during a refactor.

commit_message:
NSX: ensure dhcp port is setup on metadata network

Change in scheduling behavior caused a regression
where the dhcp port is no longer provisioned on
the (admin) metadata network created when a subnet
is uplinked to a router.

This change recovers the past behavior and extend UT
coverage to avoid further regression.

Closes-bug: #1304127

Change-Id: I8420203f68a43368f3784adb0c4cbbe55f048662

commit_message:
Update ensure()/reconnect() to catch MessagingError

The error handling code that gets connections reset if necessary
caught ConnectionError.  It really needs to catch MessagingError,
which ConnectionError inherits from.  There are other types of
MessagingErrors that may occur, such as InternalError, and they need
to cause the connection to reset, as well.

Closes-bug: #1303890
Change-Id: Ic5082b74a362ded8b35cbc75cf178fe6e0db62d0

commit_message:
Allowed nested resource metadata in POST'd samples

Fixes bug 1302664

Previously, posting samples with nested metadata caused the mongo
driver to fail on the embedded period in a metadata key.

Now, we explicitly unwind the flattened resource metadata before
publishing the sample.

Change-Id: Ibb0980afc880218962328a9b7fe792015d58d1d2
(cherry picked from commit 2e8fa7c48fe4cca5674f895bd3985dc9243a9702)

[{'created': '2014-04-08 15:13:57.000000000', 'message': 'Introduces escaping in Horizon/Orchestration

1) Escape help_text a second time to avoid bootstrap tooltip XSS issue

The "Description" parameter in a Heat template is used to populate
a help_text tooltip in the dynamically generated Heat form. Bootstrap
inserts this tooltip into the DOM using .html() which undoes any
escaping we do in Django (it should be using .text()).

This was fixed by forcing the help_text content to be escaped a second
time. The issue itself is mitigated in bootstrap.js release 2.0.3
(ours is currently 2.0.1).

2) Properly escape untrusted Heat template 'outputs'

The 'outputs' parameter in a Heat template was included in a Django
template with HTML autoescaping turned off. Malicious HTML content
could be included in a Heat template and would be rendered by Horizon
when details about a created stack were displayed.

This was fixed by not disabling autoescaping and explicitly escaping
untrusted values in any strings that are later marked "safe" to render
without further escaping.

Conflicts:
	openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/stacks/mappings.py

Change-Id: Icd9f9d9ca77068b12227d77469773a325c840001
Closes-Bug: #1289033
Co-Authored-By: Kieran Spear <kispear@gmail.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Introduces escaping in Horizon/Orchestration

1) Escape help_text a second time to avoid bootstrap tooltip XSS issue

The "Description" parameter in a Heat template is used to populate
a help_text tooltip in the dynamically generated Heat form. Bootstrap
inserts this tooltip into the DOM using .html() which undoes any
escaping we do in Django (it should be using .text()).

This was fixed by forcing the help_text content to be escaped a second
time. The issue itself is mitigated in bootstrap.js release 2.0.3
(ours is currently 2.0.1).

2) Properly escape untrusted Heat template 'outputs'

The 'outputs' parameter in a Heat template was included in a Django
template with HTML autoescaping turned off. Malicious HTML content
could be included in a Heat template and would be rendered by Horizon
when details about a created stack were displayed.

This was fixed by not disabling autoescaping and explicitly escaping
untrusted values in any strings that are later marked "safe" to render
without further escaping.

Conflicts:
	openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/stacks/mappings.py

Change-Id: Icd9f9d9ca77068b12227d77469773a325c840001
Closes-Bug: #1289033
Co-Authored-By: Kieran Spear <kispear@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Introduces escaping in Horizon/Orchestration

1) Escape help_text a second time to avoid bootstrap tooltip XSS issue

The "Description" parameter in a Heat template is used to populate
a help_text tooltip in the dynamically generated Heat form. Bootstrap
inserts this tooltip into the DOM using .html() which undoes any
escaping we do in Django (it should be using .text()).

This was fixed by forcing the help_text content to be escaped a second
time. The issue itself is mitigated in bootstrap.js release 2.0.3
(ours is currently 2.0.1).

2) Properly escape untrusted Heat template 'outputs'

The 'outputs' parameter in a Heat template was included in a Django
template with HTML autoescaping turned off. Malicious HTML content
could be included in a Heat template and would be rendered by Horizon
when details about a created stack were displayed.

This was fixed by not disabling autoescaping and explicitly escaping
untrusted values in any strings that are later marked "safe" to render
without further escaping.

Change-Id: Icd9f9d9ca77068b12227d77469773a325c840001
Closes-Bug: #1289033
Co-Authored-By: Kieran Spear <kispear@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Fix tgt target in cinder element

The package install version creates a file at /etc/tgt/conf.d/cinder.conf
and the cinder element has been adding an additional file. This would have
the effect of the source install working properly, but the package install
would end up creating volumes in /etc/cinder/volume instead of /mnt/state.

This patch changes the tgt target to be written to the existing file to
bring both the source and package installs to behave the same.

Change-Id: Ieeaa9518d6ed50595fbd70f1bbf0a17e3b5b1894

commit_message:
Introduces escaping in Horizon/Orchestration

1) Escape help_text a second time to avoid bootstrap tooltip XSS issue

The "Description" parameter in a Heat template is used to populate
a help_text tooltip in the dynamically generated Heat form. Bootstrap
inserts this tooltip into the DOM using .html() which undoes any
escaping we do in Django (it should be using .text()).

This was fixed by forcing the help_text content to be escaped a second
time. The issue itself is mitigated in bootstrap.js release 2.0.3
(ours is currently 2.0.1).

2) Properly escape untrusted Heat template 'outputs'

The 'outputs' parameter in a Heat template was included in a Django
template with HTML autoescaping turned off. Malicious HTML content
could be included in a Heat template and would be rendered by Horizon
when details about a created stack were displayed.

This was fixed by not disabling autoescaping and explicitly escaping
untrusted values in any strings that are later marked "safe" to render
without further escaping.

Change-Id: Icd9f9d9ca77068b12227d77469773a325c840001
Closes-Bug: #1289033
Co-Authored-By: Kieran Spear <kispear@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Fixes messages logged on Glance plugin retries

Retry logic is now being used for both upload_vhd and download_vhd,
but nova/virt/xenapi/client/session.py still had 'upload_vhd'
hardcoded in its logged messages. This change causes it to accept the
function being used as an argument and display that.

Fixes-Bug: #1265054
Change-Id: I6203aef81960078f92fa7839e47ee1c84df95745

commit_message:
Honor suspend/pause config switches in scenario tests

Some tests missed checking for compute features as
set in compute-feature-enabled section in tempest.conf.

Reduce double-coverage of pause/suspend tests between
basic and advanced server tests by removing pause and
suspend actions in basic ops test.

Closes-bug: 1296858

Change-Id: I80d785bb5b325ccfac3c5cfd9d076718cf587e80

commit_message:
Unify backend logging

Make account, object, and container servers construct log lines using the
same utility function so they will produce identically formatted lines.

This change reorders the fields logged for the account server.

This change also adds the "additional info" field to the two servers that
didn't log that field.  This makes the log lines identical across all 3
servers.  If people don't like that, I can take that out.  I think it makes
the documentation, parsing of the log lines, and the code a tad cleaner.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I268dc0df9dd07afa5382592a28ea37b96c6c2f44
Closes-Bug: 1280955

commit_message:
Remove hardcoded /tftpboot/ from token's tftp path

Since file to be fetched from the root tftp directory it shouldn't
contain any hardcoded path. Additionaly it eliminates bearing with
map-file containing regular expressions for tftp path replacement.

Change-Id: Iee1672834f735d7dfefce43000540522e1d053b9
Closes-Bug: #1291533

commit_message:
Correct test boundary for libvirt_driver.get_info

The test_get_domain_info_with_more_return() unit test was causing
failure on some systems where lxml was not capable of handling None for
the xml to parse. However, our unit tests should not be testing libvirt;
the unit tests in libvirt already do that. Our unit tests should simply
test the code boundaries of the unit of code that they wish to stress,
and not anything further.

This patch changes the unit test in question to only test the code
within the libvirt_driver.LibvirtDriver.get_info() method, and nothing
more, and in doing so, we remove any calls at all to libvirt and mock
out where the code passes the boundaries of the get_info() method.

Change-Id: I022cc331a980c2a4d98f16d2d77b24839b528464
Closes-bug: #1301602

Update nova's selinux policies

Nova needs permissions to /mnt/state/var/lib/nova and
/mnt/state/var/log/nova.

Remove swift container sync service

It is not required and the service definition file is not provided
in the Fedora openstack-swift-container package.

Change-Id: Ie10152e054eb1e3ffe5ce9a3f910577207606fea

commit_message:
Fix anti-affinity server-group boot failure

When the second instance is booted to an anti-affinity group
the scheduler fails with an exception due to a missing type conversion.

Closes-Bug: #1301982
Change-Id: I87b2a8d8c7d04b781c789374d6e9c7f4c8567e5d

commit_message:
Add return value to some network API methods

Add return value to api methods add_fixed_ip_to_instance() and
remove_fixed_ip_from_instance(). This allows the @refresh_cache
decorator to use returned nw_info model for updating instance
info cache instead of needing to make another rpc call to get
that same information.

Tests are added to make sure return values are used by the
refresh_cache decorator for methods where the rpc call returns
with the necessary nw_info model.

Change-Id: I748e4db9de62d82e4dbcb0b9c444b16dabf0ec5d
Partial-Bug: #1284345

commit_message:
Propose: VMware vm_ref (aka vm_util) refactor

Improper use of virtual machine references (vm_ref) in vm_util.py is the
source of many critical and high priority bugs. Refactoring this utility
so that there is one-right-way to get a virtual machine reference will
simplify the process of adding features to the driver and eliminate bugs.

related to blueprint vmware-vm-ref-refactor

Change-Id: I883ce071e91bc8c6b11a3960b093a21af026ad7b

commit_message:
Verify the create/delete volume APIs attributes

This patch adds the JSON schema for volume create & delete APIs
and validate the response of Nova Volume list APIs with added JSON
schema to block the backward incompatibility change in the future.

The response body of Nova API volume create is the below:

{
    "volume": {
        "id": "%(uuid)s",
        "status": "in-use",
        "displayName": "%(volume_name)s", null
        "availabilityZone": "zone1:host1",
        "createdAt":  "%(timestamp)s",
        "displayDescription": "%(volume_desc)s",
        "volumeType": "Backup",
        "snapshotId": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "size": 100,
        "attachments": [
            { "device": "/",
              "serverId": "%(uuid)s",
              "id": "%(uuid)s",
              "volumeId": "%(uuid)s"
            }
        ]
    }
}

delete volume API does not return any response body.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I84069dae64a70bc2a4f2313bb3da4e86630e4b1b

commit_message:
Reuse module `exceptions` from Oslo

The exception module in oslo common code and in keystoneclient are similar.
In case of unification openstack clients, we should use modules from Oslo.

Changes of this patch:
- imported exceptions from common code instead of `apiclient.exception`
- added aliases for exceptions which was renamed
(reason: backwards compatibility)
- moved exceptions `EmptyCatalog` from `apiclient.exception` to `exceptions`
- cleaned `apiclient.exception` from duplicated exceptions
- `apiclient.__init__` and `apiclient.exceptions` are kept and labeled as
'deprecated'(reason: backwards compatibility)

bp common-client-library-2

Change-Id: Iedf4e5d753d4278d81751ba0f55fdef3566b56de

commit_message:
Add service-delete command

In patch I655a7f818bb59c8971feb5841feeefafc3a4580a from nova, a new
method to the compute API was added to delete a retired service.

This patch adds support to novaclient for this with a new command called
service-delete that expects the service's id.

Change-Id: I575dbfb5f834ce88da523c80214cd2e16cc4248e

commit_message:
1288419 TypeError extending non-existent volume

If a user tries to attach a non-existant volume to an instance (open two
tabs, delete the volume in one, extend in the other) a TypeError is
raised here:

    volumes = self.get_object()
    attachments = [att for att in volumes.attachments if att]

volumes is None.

Change-Id: I5a9bbf6ac1ae315690bda9f74aa0cc837cc7540c
Closes-Bug: 1288419

commit_message:
Add standardize-nova-image blueprint

Adds blueprint specification for standardizing the nova.image module
into nova.image.api in the same way that nova.network.api works.

Change-Id: I17b3dc79c0a2286f019506e4869b23f03e15a0e7

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others

commit_message:
Fix response for missing attributes in trust

Related-Bug:#1278738

Currently, when the "impersonation" attribute is missing from the trust,
the response shows the error message provided by the backend, which is a
problem since it exposes the backend that is being used. This patch sets
the "impersonation" attribute as mandatory, as specified in the API, in
the "OpenStack Identity API v3 OS-TRUST Extension" document. Thus,
sending an appropriate error response if this attribute is missing.

Additionally, the "trustee_user_id" is now checked in the same way and
keystone will return similar response if this attribute is missing.

Change-Id: Id20fec6798e54d169662b68413591963481405c8

[{'created': '2014-04-07 21:11:35.000000000', 'message': 'Require admin context for interfaces on ext network

Currently any user can attach an interface to a neutron
external network, if the neutron plugin supports the port
binding extension.
In this case, nova will create neutron ports using the admin
client, thus bypassing neutron authZ checks for creating ports
on external networks.

This patch adds a check in nova to verify the API request has an
admin context when a request for an interface is made on a
neutron external network.

Change-Id: I5fb0bdcbf19eb82746ea3b192c1f65899bfb3c0b
Closes-Bug: 1284718
(cherry picked from commit 7d1b4117fda7709307a35e56625cfa7709a6b795)
'}]
commit_message:
Require admin context for interfaces on ext network

Currently any user can attach an interface to a neutron
external network, if the neutron plugin supports the port
binding extension.
In this case, nova will create neutron ports using the admin
client, thus bypassing neutron authZ checks for creating ports
on external networks.

This patch adds a check in nova to verify the API request has an
admin context when a request for an interface is made on a
neutron external network.

Change-Id: I5fb0bdcbf19eb82746ea3b192c1f65899bfb3c0b
Closes-Bug: 1284718
(cherry picked from commit 7d1b4117fda7709307a35e56625cfa7709a6b795)

commit_message:
Allowed nested resource metadata in POST'd samples

Fixes bug 1302664

Previously, posting samples with nested metadata caused the mongo
driver to fail on the embedded period in a metadata key.

Now, we explicitly unwind the flattened resource metadata before
publishing the sample.

Change-Id: Ibb0980afc880218962328a9b7fe792015d58d1d2

commit_message:
Minor fixes to Sahara UI Installation Guide

 * removed item #7 - it is not needed and is misleading
 * rephrased clarification for AUTO_ASSIGNMENT_ENABLED
 * renamed 'Nova Network' to 'Nova-Network' - seems like the later is
   the only name which is used

Partial-Implements: blueprint update-docs-icehouse
Change-Id: Ibb177820da8d44e1f70a8fd7273dadd57e81ad1e
(cherry picked from commit 253ab59a3bfb0066b46935edc18cb252f962877b)

commit_message:
Verify delete quota response of V2/V3 APIs

This patch adds the JSON schema for response status of Nova quota delete APIs
to block the backward incompatibility change in the future.

delete quota does not return the response body.
Response status of above APIs is below:
V2: 202
V3: 204

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I3113e3a07937bd7cb44a19e5ef4a5fb880ce3721

commit_message:
Use consistent hash type in Berksfile

This change uses consistent hash types in the Berksfile. Before
there were two different assignments:
  cookbook "statsd",
    :git => "git://github.com/att-cloud/cookbook-statsd.git"
  cookbook "openstack-common",
    git: "git://github.com/stackforge/cookbook-openstack-common.git"

This fixes that issue so they are both consistent.

Change-Id: Id20e2249b1f00a4abd90639243e4a1e600a64c47

commit_message:
Enable ServerGroup scheduler filters by default

The Icehouse release includes a server group REST API. For these
groups to actually function properly, the server group scheduler
filters must be enabled. So, these filters should be enabled by
default since the API is also enabled by default. If the API is not
used, the scheduler filters will be a no-op.

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ia52d7fcfff52377d8beae2acd9b7eba9c6c74e09
Closes-bug: #1303983

commit_message:
Add tftp conntrack modules on master node boot

Add TFTP conntrack modules to rc.modules
in order to let TFTP server in the container
function properly as Docker does natting of
TFTP traffic to the container

implements blueprint fuel-containerization-of-services

Change-Id: I5c8fae17a16ead0f842bb01f74b2207c7f14b282

commit_message:
Fix Jenkins translation jobs

The -propose-translation-update and -upstream-translation-update
jobs do not update from transifex since our po files contain
duplicate entries where obsolete entries duplicate normal entries.

Remove all obsolete entries to fix the jobs.

Change-Id: Ib0fab723f245a87bb116ca21db31841574f7dc7f
Closes-Bug: #1299349

commit_message:
Revert "Use debug level logging during unit tests"

This change made the subunit_log 190 MB on every run (14MB
in the gz version). It also dramatically increases the
memory needed to run unit tests. We need to revert and
come at this problem with fresh eyes to address the problem
at hand without effectively overrunning people's environments.

This reverts commit f9090b0bd796f8c2fdf8d0a23173f3adee71b3df.

Change-Id: Ia1cfc3d874ddf4f8ee2037b487d22f968585854e

commit_message:
Add mysql innodb buffer pool size

Innodb buffer pool size in mysql config file is now set to 592M,
this value is for VMs with 2G RAM too much. This patch makes the
pool size configurable and decreases default value to 100 MB
(this should be sufficient for default devtest setup). A patch which
for tripleo-image-element which sets this value in my.cnf will follow.

Change-Id: I0d2529abe51d4dc34415bf6c40da7a267bf3e65b

commit_message:
Delete routers that are requested but not reported as active

There are two cases that I can think of that result in a router being
requested but not reported as active.  One is that admin_state_up has
been set to False.  In this case, the router is never removed and
continues to be operational.

The other case is if a router is changed and then deleted before the
change is processed.  In this case, it is prudent to be sure that the
router is queued for deletion.

Change-Id: I4738f599a18f0d130cc8ad4d4dafc488eec75ffd
Closes-Bug: #1215387
(cherry picked from commit 9da60d0a417dd70c16ae34f5877c564e425e4cf8)

[{'created': '2014-04-08 12:18:37.000000000', 'message': "Fix _validate_mac_address method

The method _validate_mac_address previously used: netaddr.EUI(data)
which would convert data passed in to the correct mac_address representation.
For example if data=123 it would return: EUI('00-00-00-00-00-7B'). To fix
this issue I used netaddr.valid_mac() instead which returns a bool if a mac is
valid or not and does not raise. Note this file needs some improvements to
improve how exception handling is done that will come later.

Change-Id: I4fb868e40abbad9e743028cc768f47ca9b3e0e70
Closes-bug: 1291163
(cherry picked from commit b9390333a146d0435710f85d365318268e267fc3)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix _validate_mac_address method

The method _validate_mac_address previously used: netaddr.EUI(data)
which would convert data passed in to the correct mac_address representation.
For example if data=123 it would return: EUI('00-00-00-00-00-7B'). To fix
this issue I used netaddr.valid_mac() instead which returns a bool if a mac is
valid or not and does not raise. Note this file needs some improvements to
improve how exception handling is done that will come later.

Change-Id: I4fb868e40abbad9e743028cc768f47ca9b3e0e70
Closes-bug: 1291163
(cherry picked from commit b9390333a146d0435710f85d365318268e267fc3)

commit_message:
Make build_sphinx warning proof

This commit makes changes to the rst files so sphinx will not throw any
warnings. The implemented section of the index is removed, we can add
it back when a specification is implemented and we move it into that
directory.

Change-Id: I09f813623c8bdfd830f73592aac6cf57abe87741

commit_message:
Prepare network_checker for ci

Vagrant will spawn virtualbox vm with 3 interfaces
with 2 of them in same network (which will be handy for some debug)

eth1 and eth2 will be controlled by dhcp server in same network

This approach has couple of requirements:
1. virtualbox installed on jenkins node
2. vagrant installed on jenkins node
3. added precise64 box for vagrant

vagrant up - will create vm and install all necessery packages

to run tests:
vagrant ssh -c 'sudo py.test /vagrant/'

will run tests for network_checker and dhcpchecker
exit status will be non-zero in case of errors
sudo is required for capturing data on ifaces

To make docker approach to work:
1. Share linux drivers for docker containter (netchecker uses modprobe 8021q)
2. setup dnsmasq on same bridge which this docker image is using

Tests can be started on local machine with help of vde switch:
py.test --vde ./
This will create vde_switch and tap ifaces (tap11, tap12)

Related to blueprint fuel-network-checks-ci
Change-Id: Ieefca56f31db988a610870710ec9cb0ad1a0d6a6

commit_message:
Sync oslo-incubator code

Sync code to commit: b7ad6ddab8b1d61bf4f52ccaa461a9d68809747b

The oslo db API have been changed, so sqlalchemy driver have been updated
to match these changes.
We now use sqlalchemy/migration.py from oslo.db instead of the
ceilometer one.
The unused alembic code have been removed, because it is handled by
oslo.db now.

Closes bug: #1293409

Change-Id: I480d678a7165f32b92c5c9b4c55491c0edbc0991

commit_message:
Remove local engine

The local engine is replaced in process executor using the oslo.messaging
fake transport.  The local engine module is removed here along with related
unit tests. Some unit tests are rewritten to use the ScalableEngine. An
EngineTestCase is included in the base module of tests to simplify engine
testing.

Change-Id: I1a49a53eac87a209660c493fd7c3fe3e914fd092
Implements: blueprint mistral-inproc-executor
