Ah, now - from IRC.

nova/ironic/tests/__init__.py doesn't exist so discover doesn't load the tests.

Thats fixable but then oslo.config being global causes issues because we don't have all the things the driver might access available. That said - I think a fixture could work around that and make them work with a somewhat narrower setup and without needing a new job."}, {'account_id': 1420, 'date': '2014-04-02 04:13:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

rloo brought up a great point in IRC tonight during discussion of this--Juno is now open and the Ironic virt driver can/should be merged into the Nova tree. Doing that will get it tested with the rest of Nova by existing infrastructure. Making progress toward that happening + making Ironic CI a reality is a better use of time at this point IMHO.'}, {'account_id': 1420, 'date': '2014-04-02 20:22:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

commit_message:
Update tox.ini to also run nova tests

This updates testr.conf to allow passing of the tests directory as an
environment variable (defaulting to ironic/tests/). Also updates tox.ini
to run testr once for ironic/tests and once for ironic/nova/tests/, then
combine subunit output.

test-requirements.txt is updated to pull in Nova from a tarball, as well
as mox and python-ironicclient.

Updates the existing Nova driver unit tests to account for recent
refactoring and changes in the Nova virt API.

Change-Id: Ibefa2e0d3f97512f4da9ace780703fe47467232e
Closes-bug: #1299312

commit_message:
Show maintenance field in GET /nodes

Before the maintenance field was only shown if client issued a GET on
a specific node (node-show), but this is an important attribute to have
listed in a GET /nodes (node-list), it's a good info to know which nodes
from that list are in maintenance mode or not, and the Nova Ironic Driver
also need this information to determine which nodes are available to be
exposed to Nova or not.

Change-Id: Icc31a312130a1c2d5853da64bd9091a93221363c

Thanks for working through the changes we chatted about offline this morning.  For those interested: in Icehouse the Ubuntu init scripts pass the l3_agent.ini file as a --config-file argument to the VPN agent on startup.  In Havana, the init script doesn't pass the l3_agent.ini file.  It's useful in either case to able to manage this setting if you choose to use something other than br-ex as your external bridge, but setting it to undef/not present in the vpn_agent.ini file by default is safer than setting it to br-ex by default because in Icehouse we'll inherit the setting from the L3 agent config (and who knows what happens if they're set to two different things in the two files because you forget to set params for both classes)."}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2014-04-07 19:09:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Looks good to me (core reviewer); Approved

Include external network bridge for vpn agent

fix to make external network bridge configurable
in the vpn_agent.ini config file. Defaults to
nil.

commit_message:
Remove PciDeviceList usage in pci manager

Pci manager keeps a PciDeviceList and even try to append
object to the list. This is not correct, as the ObjectList
is designed as immutable, although the objects in the list is
mutable. We should simply use a list to keep devices.

Closes-Bug: #1273803

Change-Id: Ie80b6f5f47a1d2d2e20aadb4779be142c17b5b38

commit_message:
Add Ubuntu 14.04 to install guide

Icehouse is in ubuntu 14.04, which is the new Long Term Support
edition, which will eventually replace 12.04.

This adds the change needed to get it to work in the packaging
section of the install guide, and updates the labels.

Change-Id: I1008ff1b578b5a09d785b8de37b4d14ea958f236

commit_message:
Prevent creation of http images with invalid URIs

Active images should always be ready to be downloaded, regardless
they're locally or remotely stored.  This patch prevents images with
invalid location URIs from being created and entering the 'active'
state with no data.  This is only for the HTTP store.

Change-Id: Iec7a0457ffb3f937a058ad7c85b01179960a6d49
Partial-Bug: #1257273

commit_message:
Corrected 'rpc_backend' in Glance installation section

I corrected the 'rpc_backend' configuration key in
/etc/glance-api.conf to use 'rabbit' and 'qpid' values from Oslo.
I also removed extraneous AMQP configuration from
/etc/glance-registry.conf.

Change-Id: Ice9848de7fdee0df82bf35082237371e1d6ed19d
Closes-Bug: #1302976

commit_message:
Print adminPass when rebuilding from shell

The 'nova rebuild' command did not print the adminPass returned by the
server. This is because it discards the instance information returned
by the rebuild action and fetchs the information again. This would lose
the adminPass and it would not be printed for the user.

This patch reuses the instance information returned by the rebuild action
which ensures that the adminPass is printed by the shell.

Change-Id: I144bfa298bef529c78ca04042cd37a763537f09e
Closes-bug: 1302696

commit_message:
Cold Migration: pass dest nodename to virt driver

Currently, the compute manager only specifies the destination
host_ip in the migration request to the virt driver. If a driver
supports multi compute-nodes, it may need to know the destination
nodename managed by the service.

This information is already available in the migration object,
but not passed on to the virt layer.

Partial-bug: #1270332

Change-Id: I4204c580866c87711fb52924a051846ea85f0055

[{'created': '2014-04-04 19:34:07.000000000', 'message': "Fix invalid LDAP filter for user ID with comma

The Keystone server would respond with a 500 error when configured
to use the LDAP identity backend and a request is made to get a
token for a user that has an ID with a comma. The response is like:

 Authorization Failed: An unexpected error prevented the server from
 fulfilling your request. {'desc': 'Bad search filter'} (HTTP 500)

This is because the user DN wasn't properly escaped in the filter
for the query to get the groups that the user is a member of.

Closes-Bug: #1302106

Change-Id: Ib4886e66af0e979fcf23a84bcd51b07034547cb9
"}]
commit_message:
Fix invalid LDAP filter for user ID with comma

The Keystone server would respond with a 500 error when configured
to use the LDAP identity backend and a request is made to get a
token for a user that has an ID with a comma. The response is like:

 Authorization Failed: An unexpected error prevented the server from
 fulfilling your request. {'desc': 'Bad search filter'} (HTTP 500)

This is because the user DN wasn't properly escaped in the filter
for the query to get the groups that the user is a member of.

Closes-Bug: #1302106

Change-Id: Ib4886e66af0e979fcf23a84bcd51b07034547cb9

commit_message:
Removed possibility to run job w/o Oozie

* Added a validation function which checks if cluster contains oozie
  service in its node groups
* Added unit-test covers both valid and invalid cases when cluster
  contains and doesn't oozie service in attempt of job execution
* Fixed small issue in unit tests in validation utils where pathced
  api.get_cluster function had never been unpatched.

Change-Id: I5c5de6cfb1812ff6795797df63b8ec0292395fd1
Closes-Bug: #1291649

commit_message:
Taskflow 0.2 released

Taskflow 0.2 has released and should work with all
existing openstack projects as-is (integrating gating
has verified this) so unbinding and resetting the bound
at 0.3 (which does not exist yet).

Change-Id: I1e6f782c5cc6e9c54be0efc089f2876357240ac7

@Hugh Saunders, @Boris Pavlovic
Thanks for your reviews. Based on the comments of Hugh I uploaded patch set 3. It gives better results than patch set 2. However, I think there are still things that need to be addressed:
* The X axis have to start from the minimum value of the given data set, and not from 0. (Python specific)
* On the visual side of things, every tick label of the X axis should be in the end of the rectangle it represents in order to give a better notion of range. (D3.js specific)
* When you hover on a rectangle, it shows up a text that says: 'y on x'. I think that also here it needs to be changed to 'y to x' or better 'y from x-1 to x' to give again the notion of range. (D3.js specific)

To illustrate the results of every patch set, I have uploaded the HTML report of the same task.
Patch set 2: http://aetos.it.teithe.gr/~tzabal/files/rally/patchset2.html

While testing this I noticed that when the page is loaded, all atomic actions are displayed on the same histogram [0], this leads to an odd "scale" of bin values that doesn't look right. Once a specific atomic action is selected, only times for that action are shown [1]. Also after selecting one atomic action it isn't possible to get back to displaying both without reloading the page.  Perhaps it would be better to have one action pre-selected on load, if that is possible?

Add two histogram charts to the set of charts of the HTML report
produced by the 'rally task plot2html' command. The first histogram
depicts the whole task, whereas the second histogram depicts every
atomic action of the task.
Generally, the histogram has on its X axis the duration of a task
(continues variable) in seconds and separated in bins, and on its Y axis
the number of iterations.

commit_message:
Add histogram to the report of tasks' results

Add two histogram charts to the set of charts of the HTML report
produced by the 'rally task plot2html' command. The first histogram
depicts the whole task, whereas the second histogram depicts every
atomic action of the task.
For every of these two histograms, there is a drop down menu from which
the user can select the type of the histogram. The type of the histogram
is described by the method that was used to calculate the number of
bins. At the moment, there are four types and it is easy to add more.
In general, a histogram has on its X axis a continuous variable
separated in a number of bins (specific ranges) and on its Y axis the
frequency of events for every bin.
In Rally's case, the histogram has on its X axis the duration of a
benchmark scenario in seconds, separated in a number of bins, and on its
Y axis the number of iterations that fall into every defined bin.

Change-Id: Ibb8d9a7bab40a00adff25df33bac6bb0e71dfe41
Implements: blueprint cli-task-plot2html-histogram

This bug is to deprecated first_address, not remove it. It needs to be flagged as deprecated for at least one release cycle before we remove it.

This is the first attribute to be officially deprecated, and there is currently no way in the attributes_schema to do this like we can with the properties_schema. It would be nice for there to be a *very* simple Schema class for attributes schema definition which allows description and support_status to be defined. Then the docs generation can read the support_status and indicate that the attribute is deprecated.'}, {'account_id': 6577, 'date': '2014-04-07 17:07:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Abandoned

commit_message:
Remove first_address attribute of OS::Nova::Server

Currently we could use get_attr function to get necessary information
about ip addresses. So attribute first_address could be removed.

Change-Id: I8c3ad6118304a951be798117f3eaa626c7b7583d
Closes-Bug: #1302466

Nikolay - Without picking up changes in server.py & workflow.py I ran the test you provided, including the modified YAML, and had the test pass. I don't think the test proves the bug.

On the other hand after looking at your change I notice that there would be a bug in if the subsequent task (repeater_task in this case) were to be executed with a delay. In that case it would never be scheduled - is that what you are trying to fix?

If that is the case I suspect by equating IDLE and DELAYED we will actually loose the delay functionality - please verify. This also tells me that the tests I included do not contain any testing for delay - maybe I should put one in which would end up highlighting the failure I am expecting. Let me know.

In the meanwhile -1 since my opinion is this will break delay and we need to come up with an alternate mechanism to schedule a delayed task. Let me know if I am wrong."}, {'account_id': 8731, 'date': '2014-04-04 06:08:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Add resolving inline expressions

 * We allow to resolve something like:
   - /{$.project_id}/servers
   - {$.auth_token}

Change-Id: Ic2a5a32b42c168bac021ff1e96d1dae8bac6647e

commit_message:
Fix Jenkins translation jobs

The jobs nova-propose-translation-update and
nova-upstream-translation-update do not update from
transifex since our po files contain duplicate entries where
obsolete entries duplicate normal entries.

Remove all obsolete entries to fix the jobs.

Change-Id: I7f51922472f12f3a13feb71a6fb344076781d7e9
Closes-Bug: #1299349

commit_message:
Remove use of py3kcompat

Replace usage of py3kcompat.urlutils by six imports. py3kcompat has been
removed from oslo incubator so we should try to sync.

Change-Id: I252ff2b3a5284cee6e09e70a79b7dad550335f41

commit_message:
Glance: Allow configuring default_log_levels

Allow a custom value for 'default_log_levels' to be set for both the
Glance registry and API.

Allows setting 'eventlet.wsgi.server=DEBUG' which is useful for tracking
each HTTP request.

Also allows setting a log level for any middleware etc.

Change-Id: I2a791b707fd91ba2d4ca7217b5189969a110c0c9

commit_message:
Require admin context for interfaces on ext network

Currently any user can attach an interface to a neutron
external network, if the neutron plugin supports the port
binding extension.
In this case, nova will create neutron ports using the admin
client, thus bypassing neutron authZ checks for creating ports
on external networks.

This patch adds a check in nova to verify the API request has an
admin context when a request for an interface is made on a
neutron external network.

Change-Id: I5fb0bdcbf19eb82746ea3b192c1f65899bfb3c0b
Closes-Bug: 1284718

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-04-02 08:08:24.000000000', 'message': 'Added rackawareness to Hadoop 2 in vanilla plugin

* Now Hadoop 2.3.0 in vanilla is able to push topology data for
  datanodes and nodemanagers
* Only 3-level topology (rackawareness) pushes to nodes. Why 4-level is
  not? Because this is not implemented in YARN yet (see YARN-18 and YARN-19):
  https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8468
* Even if admin configures 4-level topology configs Sahara will force
  down to 3-level.

Co-Authored-By: Sergey Reshetnyak <sreshetniak@mirantis.com>

Partially implements: blueprint vanilla-plugin-hadoop-2

Change-Id: If5b93dde1f6aaaf619def60634da8c8819a3c75a

commit_message:
Added rackawareness to Hadoop 2 in vanilla plugin

* Now Hadoop 2.3.0 in vanilla is able to push topology data for
  datanodes and nodemanagers
* Only 3-level topology (rackawareness) pushes to nodes. Why 4-level is
  not? Because this is not implemented in YARN yet (see YARN-18 and YARN-19):
  https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8468
* Even if admin configures 4-level topology configs Sahara will force
  down to 3-level.

Co-Authored-By: Sergey Reshetnyak <sreshetniak@mirantis.com>

Partially implements: blueprint vanilla-plugin-hadoop-2

Change-Id: If5b93dde1f6aaaf619def60634da8c8819a3c75a

commit_message:
Remove security group egress rules

The egress security group rules were too restrictive, blocking
necessary traffic, including cloud-init metadata.
Fixes https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1080638

Change-Id: Ia11f4a81d56d76418530dab6b09478648a1cfbfd

commit_message:
Add primary folder structure for Tempest support

Adding folder structure for integration testing with Tempest.
Also, adding cli tests for basic testing functionality

Change-Id: I69896958495ddf57040a05ff73004662b7b28891
Partially implements: blueprint climate-tempest-testing

commit_message:
Updating the setup development environment docs for icehouse

Changes
* rewording title paragraph to be more descriptive of the document
* adding a link to devstack.org in the "... inside DevStack" section
* adding a sentence about developing on OSX to the "... inside DevStack"
section
* changing the toctree link to the OSX VM install doc to be inline
* minor grammar cleanup on section titles
* adding a header paragraph to the ui dev environ page
* rewording the "... as part of DevStack" section to be similar to dev
environ doc
* minor cleanups to ui dev environ page
* correcting sahara-dashboard location in /opt/stack

Partial-Implements: blueprint update-docs-icehouse

Change-Id: Ideed96512ee7f28280577f2520bacc620952e305

commit_message:
Stop removing ip allocations on port delete

The _delete_port() method was manually removing related
IPAllocation instances despite the existence of a perfectly
good cascade deletion relationship in the model.  This patch
puts an end to that nonsense and the potential for deadlock that
it represented.

Closes-bug: #1288379
Related-Bug: #1283522

Change-Id: Ib31550fa9000fc75768a327cb6cc1c419e06568f
(cherry picked from commit 2648aa3561d23e1215e0cc6f446253e5df56c8f6)

subject: Refactor to remove _recycle_ip

commit_message:
Refactor to remove _recycle_ip

Since _recycle_ip is now just a pass-through to _delete_ip_allocation
it can be removed.

Change-Id: Ifba3da902de599f748038a33ef3bd98ff77c22b9
Closes-Bug: #1269501
(cherry picked from commit 212c755c34c195148c668b553ccd9f371df63420)

subject: Simplify ip allocation/recycling to relieve db pressure

[{'created': '2014-04-01 23:32:15.000000000', 'message': "Simplify ip allocation/recycling to relieve db pressure

I found that multiple calls to delete_port can pile up on the
_recycle_ip operation.  This patch simplifies this operation.  It
reduces the _recycle_ip operation to a single row delete in the ip
allocations table and doesn't touch the availability table.

To acheive the recycling of ips in a pool, this code runs a more
complex operation of rebuilding the availability table when it is
exhausted.  Only one API process will perform this more expensive
operation and others waiting for allocation will immediately benefit.
The amortized cost of this operation is much less than the cumulative
cost of running the more expensive _recycle_ip operation for every
port delete.

IP allocation behaves a bit differently with this patch.  Instead of
giving out the first IP available in a pool, the entire pool will be
allocated before wrapping around and recycling ip addresses that have
been released.  This is a desirable feature as it puts ip addresses in
a sort of quarantine after they are released.  It is easier to
distinguish newly allocated ips from old ones.

Change-Id: Ia55b66128de9986e075b0f87acc401d211cd91d3
Closes-Bug: #1252506
Closes-Bug: #1257815
(cherry picked from commit 89f25623a4345b5044a58cff36e7fd103c6b88e8)

commit_message:
Simplify ip allocation/recycling to relieve db pressure

I found that multiple calls to delete_port can pile up on the
_recycle_ip operation.  This patch simplifies this operation.  It
reduces the _recycle_ip operation to a single row delete in the ip
allocations table and doesn't touch the availability table.

To acheive the recycling of ips in a pool, this code runs a more
complex operation of rebuilding the availability table when it is
exhausted.  Only one API process will perform this more expensive
operation and others waiting for allocation will immediately benefit.
The amortized cost of this operation is much less than the cumulative
cost of running the more expensive _recycle_ip operation for every
port delete.

IP allocation behaves a bit differently with this patch.  Instead of
giving out the first IP available in a pool, the entire pool will be
allocated before wrapping around and recycling ip addresses that have
been released.  This is a desirable feature as it puts ip addresses in
a sort of quarantine after they are released.  It is easier to
distinguish newly allocated ips from old ones.

Change-Id: Ia55b66128de9986e075b0f87acc401d211cd91d3
Closes-Bug: #1252506
Closes-Bug: #1257815
(cherry picked from commit 89f25623a4345b5044a58cff36e7fd103c6b88e8)

commit_message:
Split test_rebuild() into two tests

The method tests rebuilds with and without passwords, but the tests are
independent and should be in two seperate tests.

Also, remove duplication of the rebuild with password test from
test_rebuild_preserve_ephemeral

Change-Id: I40d0376fabf319dbe703d593de8fb4cdcf0aeab1

IMO we can go as-is and update translations in the next stable update.'}, {'account_id': 4978, 'date': '2014-04-07 08:43:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Argh, sorry for missing this.

Link to Akihiro's email about this to the list: http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-i18n/2014-April/000518.html

Could we submit a small patch to the milestone-proposed branch only (if there's time before RC2 is cut), that reverts the string to "Error updating the aggregate." since it is already translated? I probably should have done this when submitting the backport.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-04-07 16:05:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

According to the thread in I18N list, it seems better we go as-is because it is an error message and is not an usually visible string. I think we will have another translation update in the next stable update. Thanks.'}, {'account_id': 4978, 'date': '2014-04-07 16:24:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Great, thank you for following up.'}]

commit_message:
Improve Host Aggregates handle method.

Added update conditions to the handle method (remove
and add hosts).
Previously, to perform an update, first all existing hosts
were removed and then all new hosts were added.
Now, the update method only
remove or add the changed hosts.
Added missing unit tests for the update.

Change-Id: I52acdd1226be504cf2d0cf029353dbf80e4aa01a
Closes-bug: #1287192
(cherry picked from commit 8f4331a6bdc12bb7632f2d170cc94176e0897fbf)

'}, {'account_id': 5733, 'date': '2014-04-03 07:12:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Hi Akihiro. I was the one who implemented this redirect initially. The concern I had with redirecting to a panel was that the other tenant might not have access to that panel, and so get a 404/403 when the redirect happened.

As we beta-test new services like Heat or Trove, we usually give access by granting a role on a tenant, and that's one case where I think this change would fail.

That said, I would love to see a solution to this, because it's very annoying not being redirected to the same panel :)."}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-04-03 12:57:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Thanks Kieran,
the case you pointed out sounds possible and resonable use case. I agree this patch is not enough.

I think there are several ways to address it.
The one is to check permissions for destination tenant when generating drop-down menu. If a new tenant has permission to the current panel we keep the panel and otherwise it sounds good to be redirected to a parent dashboard or overview panel.
Another is if a new tenant does not have a permission to the redirected panel redirect to the parent dashboard or overview page.

I just started to study django_openstack_auth related code and I am not sure what we can, but it is good to explore a solution for this. The current behavior is annoying to me.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-04-05 10:57:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Work In Progress'}, {'account_id': 5623, 'date': '2014-04-07 15:33:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I share Kieran's concern here.  

I'm not sure how to achieve a compromise.  The logical place to make the check is in the switch method in django_openstack_auth after getting the new token.  However, that would require in memory horizon config information which django_openstack_auth shouldn't have access to.  The other option is pass the appropriate role checks as URL params to the switch method but that's a hack."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-04-07 15:33:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: No score

Starting check jobs.
http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 5623, 'date': '2014-04-07 15:35:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

"}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-04-07 16:10:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I believe I understand your concern. After that I dig into the detail in horizon and openstack_auth codes, but I don't have a good solution so far, although I usually feel frustrated the current behavior.

The same thing happens when a user has admin role with one tenant and does not with the other tenant. This leads to log out screen.

I adandone the patch and remove me from the assignee. If I have a good solution, I will try it again."}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-04-07 16:11:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Catch InstanceNotFound exceptions for V2 API instance_actions

Use the common.get_instance method to get the instance object
in the V2 API instance_actions extension rather than call
the compute api directly. The utility function
handes InstanceNotFound exceptions and tranlsates them to HTTPNotFound
rather than letting them propagate up causing a traceback.

Co-Authored-By: Michael Still <mikal@stillhq.com>

Change-Id: I1e69fed0c7c0c611fcfd48abbd4b4e0b1c8b403f
Closes-Bug: 1271146

'}]
commit_message:
Python 3: enable tests/unit/middleware/test_request_id.py

In Python 3, webob will return bytes, so we need to fix generate_request_id()
so that it also returns bytes. The behaviour is unchanged in Python 2.

Change-Id: I389cf20e4c999c9bb576a42388497852f8ba27ec

I agree with Mark that we should keep the version that's actually being run and remove the other one.

As to the quality of the tests, there was a lot of last-minute bashing on this code to get it through Tempest.  So I'm sure there are things that can and should be improved now that there's no longer a security clock ticking."}, {'account_id': 8787, 'date': '2014-04-04 16:52:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)

Please see my arguments on why the duplicate version is the one that should be removed inline.

I agree that there's much to be improved about these tests (and I don't mean just what was added in https://review.openstack.org/82840), but I think that getting rid of duplicate methods should be the first step. Having two mostly identical methods in the same class confuses the hell out of git, so we should fix that before making any more changes to this file.

If I were to make a laundry list of what's wrong with these tests, code duplication would be at the top. While cleaning that up, it would be really nice to replace mox with mock."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2014-04-05 01:56:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I agree with Dmitry on removing the new one, it's a duplicate for the most part, there is one difference with the check_image_exists call.  I realize the patch that introduced it went in quickly because it needed to be fixed for icehouse-rc1, but if someone would have noticed the duplication in the original review it would have probably not been made in the first place.

We can clean more up later."}, {'account_id': 1247, 'date': '2014-04-07 09:24:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer); Approved

commit_message:
Fix Jenkins translation jobs

The -propose-translation-update and -upstream-translation-update
jobs do not update from transifex since our po files contain
duplicate entries where obsolete entries duplicate normal entries.

Remove all obsolete entries to fix the jobs.

Change-Id: I6557c0b0c5ed73a0f87107214f5375ef1d0f8675
Closes-Bug: #1299349

commit_message:
Check that all po/pot files are valid

Perform minimal checks on po and pot files so that no broken files can

commit_message:
Report: Allow dumping to any file or function

Previously, Guru Meditation Reports were dumped to sys.stderr.
If you wished them to go elsewhere, you would have to write custom
signal handler code, duplicating most of the existing code.

Now, the setup_autorun method accepts the parameters dump_to and
dump_with.  The former dumps to the specified stream object (anything
with a write(str) method, as per the print function's documentation),
while the latter just passes the results to the whichever function is
specified (so you can pass in, for example, LOG.debug).

The signal handler accepts only dump_with (which, like version, is
expected to be curried out), so the setup_autorun method will build
a method if dump_to is passed in.

Change-Id: I8ca07b502c4cd1202f1916659fcadeeba35ab156

commit_message:
Sync latest gettextutls from oslo-incubator

Needed to prevent deep copy failures when using lazy message
evaluation.

Oslo-incubator commit included:
  fd33d1eaa0 Fix gettextutil.Message handling of deep copy failures

Last synced into Nova with Nova commit:
  5eafe1ccbe sync sslutils to not conflict with oslo.messaging

Change-Id: I1176750c5026662d02a985e04854a9ff358c11b0

Introduce keystone:config

This keystone::config is aim to use keystone_config resources
to manage custom configurations in keystone config files.

in Hiera data.

commit_message:
Excplicitly install dhcp-agent

The neutron dhcp-agent is not installed via transitive
dependencies on openSUSE. Install it expicitly.

Change-Id: Idfbb4ce615ad4396a6f040ef45503ae10f448e4a

commit_message:
Allow for stack users in _authorize_stack_user

This change allows stack user credentials to be used to call
describe_stack_resource (heat resource-metadata)

It makes the following changes:
* _authorize_stack_user first attempts authorize with
  stack.access_allowed using the context user_id before falling back
  to looking for ec2 credentials
* context middleware sets the user_id on the context even when the
  username is not specified

This change also adds missing test coverage to ContextMiddleware

Change-Id: Idb655e403ba11a3144dacf34eba0feb59ab8d911
Closes-Bug: #1299982

commit_message:
Added missing tests and checked existing ones

Some of the tests have been modified to set the implied
attributes to known values before verifying the
expectations. The ceph.client.keyring.erb template has
been deleted, any recipe was using it.

Change-Id: Ic1e5c67015290f677628d2705474d192d1d2c6dc
Closes-Bug: #1300774

commit_message:
Neutron FWaaS Tests

Tests the following operations in the Neutron API using the REST
client for Neutron:
 - List, Show, Create, Update, Delete Firewalls
 - List, Show, Create, Update, Delete Firewall Policies
 - List, Show, Create, Update, Delete Firewall Rules

Test for admin creating Firewalls, Firewall Policies and Firewall
Rules for non admin users.

Test for inserting and removing Firewall Rules from Firewall
Policies.

Change-Id: If693298e2a376be95fd3107226ecf306d393e191

commit_message:
Mock libvirt.virDomain in test_get_domain_info_with_more_return

The test was previously creating a fake virDomain but it was passing
None as XML for lxml to parse which was causing a failure.  Instead it
should be mocked out which is lighter and cleaner than the fake object.

Change-Id: I714289625cd8f52bac1c2db421df987bf12e167f
Closes-bug: #1301602

commit_message:
Add sbin directories to PATH

sbin is not part of $PATH for non interactive shells on Fedora,
we should ensure its present in all cases.

Change-Id: If5749edae6d85a0739ff5581b296cc672539686f

commit_message:
Fix Murano gate job

There were two patches which broke our gate:
1. https://review.openstack.org/#/c/80690/
   This one forces Devstack installation to fail if a project has dependencies
   not listed in the global-requirements file. Fix description:
   Devstack has two functions to install a project:
    * setup_develop
    * setup_package

   The first one does the requirements check and fails on Murano installation.
   The latter one doesn't perform any checks (it is called internally from the
   first function right after the requirements check was performed). We will
   use the latter one until all Murano requirements match global-requirements.

2. https://review.openstack.org/#/c/85032/
   This one introduced a nosetests plugin for MuranoPL. Somehow (I have no
   idea how) it breaks Tempest run in the gate. It causes our functional tests
   to behave wierdly, not recognise tempest config file and throw exception:
   "DuplicateOptError: duplicate option: use-syslog", see complete log at
   http://logs.openstack.org/13/85113/7/check/gate-murano-devstack-dsvm/4939248/console.html

   Fix description:
   Temporarily disable nosetests plugin until we figure out how to enable
   it and avoid Tempest problems in the gate.

Change-Id: I369f91fdabdc887d5ff3fb6e16d85a4d12de9f03

commit_message:
Configurable token hash algorithm

Tokens were always hashed with md5. This change allows tokens to
be hashed with sha256 (or any other algorithm supported by the
keystoneclient token hash function). This is for security
hardening.

There's a new configuration option 'hash_algorithm' in the [token]
section. If this is not set then the server's behavior is the
same as before. If it's set to a hash algorithm (such as 'sha256'),
then PKI tokens will be hashed using that algorithm. Also, the
configured hash algorithm is set on the revocation list.

SecurityImpact
DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1174499

Change-Id: I676e4235c4a4774f54ffef790a6441982281a612

commit_message:
Persist image format to a file, to prevent attacks based on changing it

The attack is based on creating a raw image that looks like a qcow2
image, and taking advantage of the code that used 'qemu-img info' to
autodetect the image format.

Now we store the image format to a 'disk.info' file, for Qcow2 and Raw
images, and only autodetect for images that have never been written to
that file.

SecurityImpact

Conflicts:
	nova/virt/libvirt/imagebackend.py

Manual tweaks to some mocking in test_imagebackend.py

Change-Id: I10ec97c6e502c9799672cf2df50e3a0f65b679a9
Co-authored-by: Nikola Dipanov <ndipanov@redhat.com>
Closes-bug: #1221190

commit_message:
InvalidCPUInfo exception added to except block

When a live migration between two nodes with different
CPU info features is launched, an InvalidCPUInfo exception
is raised and not captured. That lets the vm in an
unusable state because the task_state rollback is not
executed.

Change-Id: Ib418fa324964cabd5f342d1b764f9ac7608b7ade
Closes-Bug: #1294210

commit_message:
Fix Jenkins translation jobs

The jobs ceilometer-propose-translation-update and
ceilometer-upstream-translation-update do not update from
transifex since our po files contain duplicate entries where
obsolete entries duplicate normal entries.

Remove all obsolete entries to fix the jobs.

Add test to pep8 that checks that no new breakages get
introduced.

Change-Id: I3d7d04a7d5d073d5123f1f7b1e16fd3ef167acfb
Closes-Bug: #1299349

- Spacing/formatting updates
- Set the rpc_backend value to 'rabbit' for debian/ubuntu. This probably

commit_message:
Minor fixes for the nova section (install guide)

- Spacing/formatting updates
- Set the rpc_backend value to 'rabbit' for debian/ubuntu. This probably
  needs to be done for SUSE/RHEL ('rabbit' or 'qpid') but needs to be
  validated first.
- Simplify some examples
- On Ubuntu, remove the sqlite database before restarting the services

Change-Id: I0469e07d657ccd6a183caedf37cb0219d896be56

commit_message:
Make devtest_* accept options.

The current positional-only interface is super hard to work with.
While this patch doesn't add any new options it makes it possible
to do so without resorting to backdoor variables.

Change-Id: I7e75c462525dd1ffbcd310face5861c6358e9d71

commit_message:
Allow nginx to deploy separate from nailgun

Added new nginx.pp which owns the entire
nginx service, indepdent from main init.pp
for nailgun. Service start is optional to
compensate for LXC envs.

Added new fields for nailgun and ostf hosts
in case they are on a separate server or
container.

blueprint fuel-containerization-of-services

Change-Id: I79f10b7abc97eeb94574718e1dcf14cf5771c8cd

commit_message:
Moved security hardening HowTos from Config Ref to Cloud Admin

Moved procedures and theory over to the admin guide.
Also moved node recovery into its own file.
Edited trusted-flavor procedure with minor edits on rest.

Partial-Bug: #290687

commit_message:
Translate xml server tenantId /userId

Translate the tenantId /userId form the XML responses,
 to tenant_id/user_id to match with the json attribute names.

Start using the xml server parser on list responses.

Change-Id: I7c4b48a1ba6680d444ea5659e722905e4d4fbe12

commit_message:
Changed message when there are no IP available addresses

When trying to associate a floating IP with an instance, when
there are no more availables, the error message was changed.

Change-Id: I46a9c5ec14eea4ac27cb7f717a9e81506c808d8d
Closes-Bug: #1294042

Hey Folks,

I'd like to drop a couple of notes here w.r.t the patch format and size:

First, this patch is *huge* and it would have been really nice to have it split in smaller patches. However, this is less important now that it has been reviewed.

My second note is that, it doesn't matter whether the patch is implementing a well-defined blueprint or fixing a well-explained bug. Regardless of that, the review *has* to have a detailed commit message explaining what the patch is doing. This is useful not just for reviewers but also for future readers of this review (and the commit history). A one-line commit message is not good in any case, not even when syncing requirements from the `global-requirements`.

Just a gentle note. Great work on the patch, though!

Keep it up!"}]

commit_message:
Trailing '/' throws error

The error is seen when running against some keystone versions (details in the
bug description).

The documented way for listing services in keystone doesn't have the trailing
'/': http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-identity-service/2.0/content/GET_listServices_v2.0_OS-KSADM_services_Service_Operations_OS-KSADM.html

Additionally all the other API calls in the same file adhere to this
standard.

Change-Id: If3c13b2c46c30232071486ef8cc15492882417f9
Closes-bug: 1300397

A missing policy for validating whether an attribute should
be visible or not is a perfectly normal condition, and
there is no value in logging it.

Writing this information to the log is also having a
considerable performance impact on list operations.

Change-Id: Ie9d3ae6b249a5c49f6d81c1e56915174d8479a07

commit_message:
Don't emit log for missing attribute check policy

A missing policy for validating whether an attribute should
be visible or not is a perfectly normal condition, and
there is no value in logging it.

Writing this information to the log is also having a
considerable performance impact on list operations.

Change-Id: Ie9d3ae6b249a5c49f6d81c1e56915174d8479a07
Closes-Bug: 1302467
(cherry picked from commit ef01fb553a141c012c8d8600edd6b709c5807111)

commit_message:
Import translations from Transifex for Icehouse

* Import ~100% completed translations
  We have three languages: German, Serbian and Hindi in Icehouse :-)
* Update language list in openstack_dashboard settings.py
* Update English POT files

This commit also updates compiled PO files (.mo). There is
a discussion compiled PO files should be included in the repo
or not, but it is better to be unchanged in this release.

Update Transifex resource name in .tx/config for Icehouse.

Closes-Bug: #1300290
Change-Id: I0c378e885efc4ecdafdd5d6b027a514a5af5bb2f

commit_message:
Fix timeout for stack actions

The problem is that the timeout for running any action (i.e. create or update)
on stack is not passed from parent stack to nested stack.
All heat resources which are internally implemented as StackResource are
affected. For example AutoScalingGroup always using default timeout
(60 minutes). If creating any of the instances will take more that it will
fail no matter what timeout you will pass creating stack.

Changes:
* removes hardcoded timeout (60 minutes)
* adds new config option to specify timeout for stack action
* if timeout was not specified for nested stack then timeout from parent
  is used
* adds test for StackResource and parser.Stack

Change-Id: I39494b75774988c625cb22cc7873d628c04d3228
Closes-Bug: 1287719

commit_message:
Move module level setup under setup_package method

Perform all the package level test setup under the setup_package
method so that we only read the configuration file on disk when
functional tests are run. This let's us "play nice" with other tests.

Change-Id: I699d664bcef6754aac4ec6877830e745b764342f

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-04-04 22:47:44.000000000', 'message': 'ML2: ODL driver sets port status

The OpenDaylight mechanism driver does not depend on an L2 agent to
plug the port. Now that nova waits for notification that the port
status is ACTIVE, the ML2 driver API is extended so that the mechanism
driver that binds a port can optionally set the port status, and the
OpenDaylight mechanism driver uses this to set the port status to
ACTIVE.

Closes-Bug: 1301449
Change-Id: I171c405f36b4f2354d9585e8ae3dfa50ddaa9a7e
(cherry picked from commit a9e3074aa9f442c2fff1ba058ac8ed585c6caa24)

commit_message:
ML2: ODL driver sets port status

The OpenDaylight mechanism driver does not depend on an L2 agent to
plug the port. Now that nova waits for notification that the port
status is ACTIVE, the ML2 driver API is extended so that the mechanism
driver that binds a port can optionally set the port status, and the
OpenDaylight mechanism driver uses this to set the port status to
ACTIVE.

Closes-Bug: 1301449
Change-Id: I171c405f36b4f2354d9585e8ae3dfa50ddaa9a7e
(cherry picked from commit a9e3074aa9f442c2fff1ba058ac8ed585c6caa24)

commit_message:
Setup nameservers in the default-net.

Its not useful to have no DNS. Long term we probably need to make
this configurable, but 8.8.8.8 is sane for many environments.

Change-Id: I732e6a1b93d7d8ab2f8f37646db38454e4088483

[{'created': '2014-02-16 21:31:47.000000000', 'message': 'Fix invalid facilities documented in rootwrap.conf

The values user0 and user1 do not map to valid facility values.
local1, etc.  Using user0 results in a  pri value that does not map
back to a facility of the same name in syslog.

RFC5424 suggest values values of local0 through local7.  Setting
syslog_log_facility to one of those values results in a message with a
priority that can be mapped back to the original string value.

This fix adjusts the comment in rootwrap.conf to suggest the local
prefix instead of the user prefix.

Closes-Bug #1280879

Change-Id: Ibefffb5619641b75b4f8ac8ce8112a34cf03f0ce
'}]
commit_message:
Fix invalid facilities documented in rootwrap.conf

The values user0 and user1 do not map to valid facility values.
local1, etc.  Using user0 results in a  pri value that does not map
back to a facility of the same name in syslog.

RFC5424 suggest values values of local0 through local7.  Setting
syslog_log_facility to one of those values results in a message with a
priority that can be mapped back to the original string value.

This fix adjusts the comment in rootwrap.conf to suggest the local
prefix instead of the user prefix.

Closes-Bug #1280879

Change-Id: Ibefffb5619641b75b4f8ac8ce8112a34cf03f0ce

commit_message:
Add 'load url from future' for django compat

Django 1.3 had a correction to inconsistency with the 'url' tag;
versions of Django pre 1.5 expect the old behavior, and best
practice is to use '{% load url from future %}' whereever the 'url'
tag is used. This was missing from some of the newer catalog templates.

Change-Id: I78b51027ff892e140a8b48e1df09e837358cfb8d
Closes-Bug: 1302834

commit_message:
Add configurable handler selection for Worker

Added to solum-worker the configuration value 'handler'
to select which one of the available modules in its
handlers directory to use as its endpoint. The result is
being able to configure exactly how images will be built.

At present we only have shell.py, which uses subprocess
to run the build-app script, but in the future there may
be other handlers to use perhaps Jenkins or another process.

Since worker already had shell.py, I have added default.py
mainly for contract enforcement, and so there is a default
to fall back upon should shell.py be unsuitable to a user.

Change-Id: Ic9a40cbef111ef3c28c6d629dd4209398d1d52ae

This reverts commit 665352f169a7d1e7eca590d466241cc313adb7c3.

commit_message:
Test for lock wait timeout

On update vips and update port status
These account for more than 50% of lock wait timeout erros.

This patch also mitigates a source of intermittent failures
in radware's load balancing driver unit tests.

Bug: #TBD
Change-Id: I94bade92a7db90b30dcb1567d31f44fb11440935
